WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:22.759 --> 00:00:25.333
♪♪[Woman Vocalizing ]

3
00:01:04.216 --> 00:01:06.090
[ Bird Squawking ]

4
00:01:06.218 --> 00:01:08.092
[ Dog Barking ]

5
00:01:08.220 --> 00:01:12.431
- [ Girl ] Buglar. make it stop!
- I can't! I can't!

6
00:01:12.557 --> 00:01:14.550
- Please! [ Crying ]
- [ Boy Screaming ] Mama!

7
00:01:15.039 --> 00:01:18.426
[ Dog Growling. Whimpering ]

8
00:01:18.563 --> 00:01:20.805
- [ Screaming ]
- Make it stop. please!

9
00:01:22.567 --> 00:01:25.105
- [ Whimpering Continues ]
- [ Boy ] Mama. help me!

10
00:01:27.238 --> 00:01:29.361
- [ Boy Screaming ]
- [ Girl ] Here. Boy!

11
00:01:29.490 --> 00:01:31.613
[ Crying ]

12
00:01:31.742 --> 00:01:35.158
[ Whimpering Continues ]

13
00:01:39.124 --> 00:01:42.956
- Oh. Grandma Baby.
- Mmm-mm.

14
00:01:55.849 --> 00:01:57.640
Shh!

15
00:01:57.767 --> 00:02:00.934
- We're gonna need some food. Wait here.
- Okay.

16
00:02:06.693 --> 00:02:08.602
[ Here Boy Whimpering ]

17
00:02:11.447 --> 00:02:13.321
Good boy. Here Boy.

18
00:02:35.637 --> 00:02:37.012
Howard. come on!

19
00:02:39.975 --> 00:02:43.011
- Come on.
- Howard. Buglar!

20
00:02:43.144 --> 00:02:45.018
Where you goin'?

21
00:02:45.146 --> 00:02:46.521
- Bye. Denver.
- Bye?

22
00:02:48.483 --> 00:02:50.641
- [ Gasps ]
- We gotta go!

23
00:02:54.155 --> 00:02:56.231
- [ Crying ]
- Buglar. come on.

24
00:02:57.472 --> 00:03:01.137
- No! Buge!
- Go ahead.

25
00:03:01.162 --> 00:03:03.035
Howard!

26
00:03:16.218 --> 00:03:19.135
Now what'd you go
and do that for?

27
00:03:20.805 --> 00:03:22.715
[ Panting ]

28
00:03:29.522 --> 00:03:31.396
Mama.

29
00:04:02.512 --> 00:04:05.430
[ Hoof beats Clattering ]

30
00:04:08.268 --> 00:04:10.640
♪♪ [ Woman Vocalizing ]

31
00:04:52.936 --> 00:04:55.806
[ Barking ]

32
00:04:57.231 --> 00:05:00.019
Watch out there. Here Boy.

33
00:05:00.151 --> 00:05:02.025
[ Child Crying ]

34
00:05:18.418 --> 00:05:20.328
[ Barking ]

35
00:05:57.039 --> 00:05:58.913
Paul?

36
00:06:01.043 --> 00:06:02.916
Paul D?

37
00:06:04.046 --> 00:06:06.750
Is that you?

38
00:06:06.882 --> 00:06:08.755
What's left.

39
00:06:08.884 --> 00:06:12.050
[ Hoof beats Clattering ]

40
00:06:13.138 --> 00:06:16.471
How you been. girl?
Besides barefoot.

41
00:06:18.700 --> 00:06:21.156
Messed up my legs back yonder.

42
00:06:21.757 --> 00:06:23.221
Chamomile.

43
00:06:23.314 --> 00:06:25.472
I don't even
wanna hear about it.

44
00:06:25.608 --> 00:06:27.482
I always did hate that stuff.

45
00:06:27.610 --> 00:06:30.279
You're lookin' good.

46
00:06:30.404 --> 00:06:33.026
Devil's confusion. Sethe.

47
00:06:33.115 --> 00:06:36.566
He lets me look good
as long as I feel bad.

48
00:06:38.153 --> 00:06:40.152
How long has it been?

49
00:06:45.043 --> 00:06:47.000
Eighteen years.

50
00:06:48.839 --> 00:06:51.412
Eighteen years?

51
00:06:51.550 --> 00:06:54.883
I swear. I've been walkin'
every one of 'em.

52
00:06:56.554 --> 00:06:57.584
Mind if I join you?

53
00:06:57.767 --> 00:06:59.908
You wanna soak 'em?
Let me get you some water.

54
00:06:59.933 --> 00:07:02.761
No. Can't baby feet.

55
00:07:02.840 --> 00:07:06.144
They's got a whole lot more
trampling to do.

56
00:07:06.169 --> 00:07:08.327
[ Sighing ]

57
00:07:08.566 --> 00:07:11.602
You ain't leavin' right away.
You stay awhile.

58
00:07:11.736 --> 00:07:15.520
Ah. well. long enough
to see Baby Suggs...

59
00:07:15.656 --> 00:07:17.613
and you.

60
00:07:17.741 --> 00:07:20.067
Where is she?

61
00:07:20.160 --> 00:07:22.070
Dead.

62
00:07:24.957 --> 00:07:26.949
Oh. no.

63
00:07:27.042 --> 00:07:31.040
- When?
- Eight years ago now.

64
00:07:31.171 --> 00:07:33.543
Almost nine.

65
00:07:33.673 --> 00:07:38.300
Was it hard?
I hope she didn't die hard.

66
00:07:38.428 --> 00:07:41.049
Soft as cream.

67
00:07:41.181 --> 00:07:44.384
Bein' alive was the hard part.

68
00:07:44.517 --> 00:07:46.973
Sorry you missed her. though.

69
00:07:47.103 --> 00:07:49.179
Is that what you came by for?

70
00:07:50.815 --> 00:07:53.816
That's some of what I came for.

71
00:07:54.599 --> 00:07:55.817
Rest is you.

72
00:07:58.697 --> 00:08:02.695
[ Sighs ] Truth be known...

73
00:08:02.826 --> 00:08:06.030
these days I go anywhere
they let me sit down.

74
00:08:09.750 --> 00:08:13.534
I wouldn't have to ask you
about him. would I?

75
00:08:15.047 --> 00:08:18.297
You'd tell me if there was
anything to tell. wouldn't you?

76
00:08:18.383 --> 00:08:20.791
I'd tell you.
You know I would.

77
00:08:22.012 --> 00:08:23.885
So you don't know
nothin' either.

78
00:08:26.099 --> 00:08:31.176
[ Sighs ] Halle. Halle.
[ Grunts ]

79
00:08:31.312 --> 00:08:33.186
[ Horse Whinnying ]

80
00:08:47.494 --> 00:08:49.866
We got spare rooms.

81
00:08:51.498 --> 00:08:54.036
Could stay the night
if you had the mind to.

82
00:08:54.126 --> 00:08:56.118
You don't sound too steady
in the offer.

83
00:08:56.253 --> 00:08:59.040
Oh. it's truly meant.

84
00:08:59.131 --> 00:09:01.372
It's just that I hope
you'll pardon my house.

85
00:09:01.466 --> 00:09:03.375
"My house."

86
00:09:06.054 --> 00:09:09.090
I like the sound of that.

87
00:09:09.265 --> 00:09:11.092
Come on in.

88
00:09:17.106 --> 00:09:19.099
- Come on in.
- [ Chuckling ]

89
00:09:32.162 --> 00:09:36.076
Good God. girl.
What kind of evil you got in there?

90
00:09:36.166 --> 00:09:39.500
It ain't evil.
Just sad. Come on.

91
00:09:39.628 --> 00:09:41.501
Step on through.

92
00:10:52.072 --> 00:10:54.480
I-I thought you said
she died soft.

93
00:10:54.575 --> 00:10:57.148
That's not Baby Suggs.

94
00:10:58.328 --> 00:11:00.998
- Who then?
- My daughter.

95
00:11:02.874 --> 00:11:05.540
The one I sent ahead with
the boys before I run off.

96
00:11:05.564 --> 00:11:06.604
She didn't live?

97
00:11:06.887 --> 00:11:09.036
- No.
- Boys too?

98
00:11:09.172 --> 00:11:11.165
No. they alive. I pray.

99
00:11:11.299 --> 00:11:14.668
They run off just before
Baby Suggs went and died.

100
00:11:19.265 --> 00:11:22.515
Probably best. Ahh!

101
00:11:22.602 --> 00:11:25.057
Negro boy got legs.
he ought to use 'em.

102
00:11:25.188 --> 00:11:29.019
Sit around too long. somebody'll
figure out a way to tie 'em up.

103
00:11:29.108 --> 00:11:31.860
Ahh!

104
00:11:37.908 --> 00:11:41.028
- By yourself then?
- No.

105
00:11:41.414 --> 00:11:44.370
Got the girl I was carryin'
when I left Sweet Home.

106
00:11:44.456 --> 00:11:49.699
You had that baby. did you?
Damn. I didn't think you'd make it.

107
00:11:49.795 --> 00:11:52.712
Runnin' off pregnant.
all by yourself too.

108
00:11:52.881 --> 00:11:54.708
- [ Footsteps ]
- Denver!

109
00:11:57.385 --> 00:11:59.259
Come here. baby.

110
00:11:59.387 --> 00:12:01.593
I want you to meet somebody.

111
00:12:04.934 --> 00:12:07.092
Paul D. this here is my Denver.

112
00:12:12.584 --> 00:12:15.476
Uh. mornin'. Miss Denver.
It's a pleasure.

113
00:12:23.064 --> 00:12:24.658
Mornin'. Mr D.

114
00:12:24.786 --> 00:12:29.911
Uh. Garner. baby.
Paul D Garner.

115
00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:32.573
- Yes. sir.
- Glad to get a look at you.

116
00:12:32.711 --> 00:12:35.166
She a fine-lookin'
young lady. Sethe.

117
00:12:35.297 --> 00:12:38.962
Yeah. Got her daddy's
sweet face.

118
00:12:39.092 --> 00:12:40.420
You know my daddy?

119
00:12:40.510 --> 00:12:44.460
Of course he know your daddy.
He from Sweet Home.

120
00:12:44.597 --> 00:12:47.088
Yeah.

121
00:12:47.183 --> 00:12:49.092
Sweet Home.

122
00:12:50.978 --> 00:12:54.762
How come everybody who run off from
Sweet Home can't stop talkin' about it?

123
00:12:54.899 --> 00:12:58.149
It looks like if it was so sweet.
you wouldn't run away.

124
00:12:58.277 --> 00:13:01.112
Girl. who you think
you talkin' to?

125
00:13:01.196 --> 00:13:03.734
True. true.
She-She right. Sethe.

126
00:13:03.824 --> 00:13:08.450
It wasn't sweet.
and it sure wasn't home.

127
00:13:08.537 --> 00:13:12.617
But it's where we were.
all together.

128
00:13:12.749 --> 00:13:16.035
Come back whether
we wanted to or not.

129
00:13:19.422 --> 00:13:21.296
[ Sighs ]

130
00:13:22.634 --> 00:13:24.543
We have a ghost here. you know?

131
00:13:24.677 --> 00:13:27.844
- [ Liquid Pouring ]
- We met.

132
00:13:27.978 --> 00:13:29.722
Denver. heat up that stove.

133
00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:33.218
Can't have a friend stop by
and don't feed him.

134
00:13:33.352 --> 00:13:35.594
Oh. don't go to no trouble
on my account.

135
00:13:35.688 --> 00:13:38.309
Bread ain't no trouble.

136
00:13:38.441 --> 00:13:40.813
The rest I bring back
from where I work.

137
00:13:40.903 --> 00:13:44.380
Least I can do workin' dawn to noon
is bring home supper.

138
00:13:44.405 --> 00:13:46.237
Got any objections to pike?

139
00:13:46.365 --> 00:13:48.856
If he don't object to me.
I don't object to him.

140
00:13:53.705 --> 00:13:55.994
Why don't you spend the night.
Mr Garner?

141
00:13:56.124 --> 00:13:59.659
That way. two of you can talk
about Sweet Home all night long.

142
00:14:00.381 --> 00:14:02.291
Denver. what is the matter
with you?

143
00:14:02.380 --> 00:14:04.337
I never known you
to behave this way.

144
00:14:04.466 --> 00:14:06.339
[ Crying ]

145
00:14:08.931 --> 00:14:11.090
[ Sniffling ]
Mama. I can't no more.

146
00:14:12.223 --> 00:14:14.097
[ Sniffling Continues ]

147
00:14:15.142 --> 00:14:17.016
I can't no more.

148
00:14:17.103 --> 00:14:19.095
You can't what?
What can't you?

149
00:14:19.230 --> 00:14:21.103
Can't live here.

150
00:14:23.339 --> 00:14:26.378
I don't know where I'ma go
or what I'ma do...

151
00:14:26.403 --> 00:14:28.360
but I can't stay here!

152
00:14:28.489 --> 00:14:31.193
[ Sobbing ]

153
00:14:31.325 --> 00:14:34.616
Nobody speaks to us.
nobody comes by...

154
00:14:34.641 --> 00:14:38.243
nobody even knows I'm alive.

155
00:14:38.373 --> 00:14:40.366
Oh. Denver.

156
00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:42.374
Come here. baby.

157
00:14:44.421 --> 00:14:46.378
- It's all right.
- Sethe.

158
00:14:46.464 --> 00:14:48.373
I'm a grown man...

159
00:14:49.717 --> 00:14:51.876
with nothin' new
left to see or do...

160
00:14:51.970 --> 00:14:54.377
but I tell you
it can't be easy...

161
00:14:54.472 --> 00:14:56.797
a young girl
livin' in a haunted place.

162
00:14:57.200 --> 00:14:59.056
Maybe you ought to move.

163
00:14:59.143 --> 00:15:01.052
No.

164
00:15:01.145 --> 00:15:04.810
No movin'. No leavin'.

165
00:15:04.940 --> 00:15:07.147
It's all right the way it is.
It's all right.

166
00:15:07.276 --> 00:15:09.601
You wanna tell me
it's all right. Sethe...

167
00:15:09.737 --> 00:15:11.901
and that child's half
outta her mind.

168
00:15:11.926 --> 00:15:13.398
[ Clattering ]

169
00:15:15.158 --> 00:15:17.910
- [ Denver Whimpering ]
- Hush. I say!

170
00:15:19.546 --> 00:15:22.906
I got a tree on my back...

171
00:15:22.999 --> 00:15:25.206
and a haint in my house...

172
00:15:25.293 --> 00:15:27.784
and nothin' in between but the daughter
I'm holdin' in my arms.

173
00:15:27.921 --> 00:15:31.206
No leavin'.
No runnin' from nothin'.

174
00:15:31.299 --> 00:15:33.457
- You hear me?
- [ Mumbling ]

175
00:15:33.593 --> 00:15:37.756
I will never run from another thing
on this Earth.

176
00:15:41.642 --> 00:15:43.551
Come on.

177
00:15:43.644 --> 00:15:46.148
You can sit down and eat...

178
00:15:46.173 --> 00:15:49.174
- or you can leave us be.
- [ Sobbing ]

179
00:16:13.882 --> 00:16:16.633
[ Grunts ]

180
00:16:16.718 --> 00:16:18.627
Lord.

181
00:16:29.188 --> 00:16:31.062
What tree. Sethe?

182
00:16:34.902 --> 00:16:36.941
Huh?

183
00:16:38.197 --> 00:16:40.569
I don't see nothin'
growin' on your back.

184
00:16:43.702 --> 00:16:46.109
It's there all the same.

185
00:16:46.204 --> 00:16:48.363
Chokecherry tree.

186
00:16:50.041 --> 00:16:51.950
Leaves. branches.

187
00:16:54.013 --> 00:16:56.835
That was 18 years ago.

188
00:16:56.943 --> 00:16:59.403
- Happened that night.
- That night?

189
00:16:59.428 --> 00:17:00.606
[ Screaming ]

190
00:17:00.752 --> 00:17:03.356
Tree could have cherries
by now for all I know.

191
00:17:03.971 --> 00:17:07.056
I ain't followin' you. Sethe.

192
00:17:07.183 --> 00:17:09.056
I had milk. Paul D.

193
00:17:09.185 --> 00:17:10.513
[ Chattering ]

194
00:17:10.644 --> 00:17:12.518
I had milk. see?

195
00:17:14.273 --> 00:17:17.190
I was pregnant with Denver...

196
00:17:18.037 --> 00:17:20.111
but I hadn't stopped nursin'
my baby girl...

197
00:17:20.237 --> 00:17:23.072
before I sent her and the
boys off with Thirty-Mile Woman.

198
00:17:23.198 --> 00:17:24.989
[ Crying ]

199
00:17:25.075 --> 00:17:30.282
All I knew was.
I had to get milk to my baby girl.

200
00:17:30.413 --> 00:17:32.739
I thought we was talkin'
about a tree.

201
00:17:33.207 --> 00:17:37.203
We was all supposed to meet
in the cornfield. None of you came.

202
00:17:37.337 --> 00:17:41.548
I had to leave my children.
go back lookin' for Halle.

203
00:17:41.633 --> 00:17:43.542
That's when I saw you
in the shed.

204
00:17:43.567 --> 00:17:46.788
Sixo dead. Schoolteacher
done gone and burnt him.

205
00:17:46.813 --> 00:17:48.672
Paul A too.
They hang him from a tree.

206
00:17:48.764 --> 00:17:52.050
Said you were gonna run
no matter what.

207
00:17:52.143 --> 00:17:54.219
I didn't think you would
make it to the gate.

208
00:17:54.699 --> 00:17:57.076
I went back in the barn
to look for Halle.

209
00:17:57.246 --> 00:17:58.248
Animal.

210
00:17:58.273 --> 00:18:00.223
That's when
Schoolteacher saw me.

211
00:18:00.359 --> 00:18:01.901
[ Schoolteacher ]
What's it taste like?

212
00:18:02.027 --> 00:18:04.480
Came in there
with his boys after me.

213
00:18:04.505 --> 00:18:07.126
You've got
animal characteristics.

214
00:18:07.878 --> 00:18:09.731
Them boys took my milk.

215
00:18:09.826 --> 00:18:12.531
That's my baby's food!

216
00:18:13.843 --> 00:18:15.456
That's what
they come in there for.

217
00:18:15.582 --> 00:18:18.287
[ Screaming ]

218
00:18:18.874 --> 00:18:21.917
Hold me down. take it.

219
00:18:23.811 --> 00:18:25.374
I told Miss Garner on 'em.

220
00:18:25.466 --> 00:18:27.091
[ Sethe ]
They're lyin'. the animals!

221
00:18:29.753 --> 00:18:32.458
She had that lump on
her neck and couldn't speak.

222
00:18:33.029 --> 00:18:35.766
But her eyes rolled out tears.
I remember.

223
00:18:38.145 --> 00:18:40.221
Them boys found out
I told on 'em.

224
00:18:40.307 --> 00:18:44.933
- [ Screaming ]
- You're horrible and beaten up!

225
00:18:45.069 --> 00:18:46.942
You're horrible and beaten up!

226
00:18:46.967 --> 00:18:49.941
Schoolteacher had one of 'em
whoopin' up my back.

227
00:18:51.658 --> 00:18:54.066
And when it closed...

228
00:18:56.830 --> 00:18:58.739
it left a tree.

229
00:19:03.753 --> 00:19:05.829
They used cowhide on you.

230
00:19:12.970 --> 00:19:14.844
And they took my milk.

231
00:19:17.183 --> 00:19:20.267
They beat you
and you was pregnant?

232
00:19:22.021 --> 00:19:24.428
And they took my milk.

233
00:20:09.900 --> 00:20:12.569
Oh. Lord. girl.

234
00:20:22.078 --> 00:20:24.996
[ Clattering. Baby Crying ]

235
00:20:32.020 --> 00:20:34.226
[ Crying Continues ]

236
00:20:44.767 --> 00:20:46.724
[ Screaming ]

237
00:20:46.810 --> 00:20:49.562
[ Screaming ] Goddam it!

238
00:20:49.647 --> 00:20:52.351
Hush up!

239
00:20:52.441 --> 00:20:54.184
[ Barking ]

240
00:20:54.554 --> 00:20:56.767
[ Sethe ]
Denver! Denver!

241
00:20:56.904 --> 00:20:58.730
Move! Move!

242
00:20:58.822 --> 00:21:00.898
Get outta the way!

243
00:21:00.991 --> 00:21:03.398
[ Paul D ]
Leave this place alone!

244
00:21:07.914 --> 00:21:10.535
I said. hush up. goddam it!

245
00:21:10.625 --> 00:21:13.522
Paul D. look out!

246
00:21:16.033 --> 00:21:17.379
Paul D!

247
00:21:17.465 --> 00:21:20.134
[ Paul D Groaning ]

248
00:21:25.014 --> 00:21:28.596
- Paul D!
- You wanna fight?

249
00:21:30.265 --> 00:21:34.511
Then come on. goddam it!
[ Yelling ]

250
00:21:38.569 --> 00:21:40.442
[ Panting ]

251
00:21:50.997 --> 00:21:53.405
[ Birds Twittering ]

252
00:22:04.802 --> 00:22:06.676
[ Panting Continues ]

253
00:22:30.201 --> 00:22:32.075
[ Coughing ]

254
00:25:02.181 --> 00:25:04.588
[ Chickens Clucking ]

255
00:25:23.952 --> 00:25:25.825
[ Baby Cooing ]

256
00:25:25.954 --> 00:25:28.789
- [ Man ] I was up there in the loft!
- [ Paul D Screaming ] Halle!

257
00:25:28.873 --> 00:25:31.660
- [ Sethe ] Them boys took my milk.
- Halle!

258
00:25:31.751 --> 00:25:34.668
- That's what they come in there for.
- [ Halle ] The loft. the loft.

259
00:25:34.796 --> 00:25:36.669
- Halle!
- I seen it all!

260
00:25:36.797 --> 00:25:41.127
- [ Sethe ] Hold me down and take it.
- [ Screaming ]

261
00:25:41.218 --> 00:25:42.160
[ Gasping ]

262
00:25:42.185 --> 00:25:44.622
- Halle!
- Milk it like a cow.

263
00:25:44.647 --> 00:25:46.794
That's what we mean
by animal characteristics.

264
00:25:46.819 --> 00:25:48.819
Halle! Stop!

265
00:26:17.295 --> 00:26:19.501
[ Paul D ]
♪ Little rice ♪

266
00:26:19.589 --> 00:26:21.877
♪ Little bean ♪

267
00:26:21.966 --> 00:26:26.343
♪ No meat in between ♪

268
00:26:26.428 --> 00:26:29.346
♪ Hard work ain't easy ♪♪

269
00:26:29.431 --> 00:26:31.340
[ Sethe ] Anybody here?

270
00:26:31.365 --> 00:26:34.319
Mama! Mama!

271
00:26:34.424 --> 00:26:36.666
[ Chuckling ]

272
00:26:39.107 --> 00:26:42.108
- Sethe? [ Clears Throat ]
- Hmm?

273
00:26:42.235 --> 00:26:45.355
I was thinkin'
of lookin' for work around here.

274
00:26:45.447 --> 00:26:48.863
- What you think?
- Hmm. Ain't much.

275
00:26:48.950 --> 00:26:51.867
River mostly. And hogs.

276
00:26:51.953 --> 00:26:54.195
Well. I never worked
on the river...

277
00:26:54.289 --> 00:26:57.159
but I can pick up anything
heavy as me. hogs included.

278
00:26:57.251 --> 00:27:00.537
White folks here
better than Kentucky. but...

279
00:27:00.670 --> 00:27:03.421
you just might
have to scramble some.

280
00:27:03.547 --> 00:27:06.501
Well. it ain't whether I scramble.
it's where.

281
00:27:06.634 --> 00:27:09.800
You sayin' it's all right
to scramble here?

282
00:27:10.108 --> 00:27:12.396
Better than all right.

283
00:27:13.610 --> 00:27:17.477
Your girl. Denver. it seems she
of a different mind though.

284
00:27:17.728 --> 00:27:20.100
You don't never have
to worry about Denver.

285
00:27:20.188 --> 00:27:24.103
She a charmed child
from the beginning.

286
00:27:24.234 --> 00:27:26.939
Gotta know one thing
though. Paul D.

287
00:27:26.994 --> 00:27:29.117
This here ain't no better life.

288
00:27:29.281 --> 00:27:31.190
Just not that other one.

289
00:27:31.310 --> 00:27:33.968
What I do here--
all I ever do...

290
00:27:33.993 --> 00:27:37.409
is keep Denver
from that other one.

291
00:27:37.497 --> 00:27:41.115
Won't let the past in my yard again.
You understand?

292
00:27:41.209 --> 00:27:44.044
Dangerous to love any one thing
that much. Sethe.

293
00:27:44.170 --> 00:27:47.040
The best thing is to love everything
just a little bit.

294
00:27:47.173 --> 00:27:51.633
That way. if it breaks or runs off
or is taken away...

295
00:27:51.665 --> 00:27:53.704
you know. maybe. you still have
a little love left over.

296
00:27:53.759 --> 00:27:57.128
Hmm. Well. that's the way
it is. Paul D.

297
00:27:57.349 --> 00:28:01.845
If I have to choose.
well. ain't no choice.

298
00:28:01.979 --> 00:28:04.814
That's the whole point.
I ain't askin' you to choose.

299
00:28:04.940 --> 00:28:08.640
I just wanna know
if there's a place for me.

300
00:28:08.735 --> 00:28:12.483
If there's more than.
"You can stay. it's fine."

301
00:28:12.614 --> 00:28:15.484
More like.
"I want you here. Paul."

302
00:28:16.951 --> 00:28:21.163
Maybe we ought to just leave things
the way they are.

303
00:28:21.247 --> 00:28:25.494
Sethe. I'm not sayin' this
'cause I need a place to stay.

304
00:28:26.121 --> 00:28:29.665
We could make a life. girl.
A life.

305
00:28:30.170 --> 00:28:33.516
- I don't know about that. Paul D Garner.
- Leave it to me!

306
00:28:33.750 --> 00:28:37.341
See how it goes. No promises
if you don't wanna make none.

307
00:28:37.429 --> 00:28:40.216
Just leave it to me.
All right?

308
00:28:40.349 --> 00:28:42.258
[ Hoof beats Clattering ]

309
00:28:42.392 --> 00:28:45.642
- All right. we'll see how it goes.
- [ Sighing ]

310
00:28:45.729 --> 00:28:49.477
You're willin'
to leave it to me?

311
00:28:50.018 --> 00:28:51.475
Some of it.

312
00:28:51.939 --> 00:28:55.696
Some. Okay. Okay.

313
00:28:55.822 --> 00:28:58.989
Here's some.
There's a carnival in town.

314
00:28:59.075 --> 00:29:01.531
Thursdays for coloreds.
and I got two dollars.

315
00:29:01.619 --> 00:29:04.537
Me. you and Denver
gonna spend every penny.

316
00:29:04.622 --> 00:29:07.539
- What you say?
- I don't know.

317
00:29:08.330 --> 00:29:09.540
All right?

318
00:29:13.381 --> 00:29:16.255
- No.
- Aw-- Please!

319
00:29:22.914 --> 00:29:25.592
[ Denver ]
You think Baby Ghost's really gone?

320
00:29:27.769 --> 00:29:29.678
Don't know.

321
00:29:30.939 --> 00:29:33.560
She my sister.

322
00:29:33.692 --> 00:29:35.565
I miss her.

323
00:29:38.071 --> 00:29:43.065
[ Paul D ]
♪ Well. I said come here. black woman ♪

324
00:29:43.201 --> 00:29:45.988
I wish he'd shut up.
He gonna ruin everything.

325
00:29:46.120 --> 00:29:50.034
- Shh. Give him a chance.
- ♪♪ [ Singing Continues ]

326
00:29:50.124 --> 00:29:52.532
- Do that for me.
- Why?

327
00:29:52.627 --> 00:29:54.536
How long he stayin'?

328
00:29:56.672 --> 00:30:01.583
- Don't know.
- ♪ I said run here. black woman ♪

329
00:30:01.677 --> 00:30:06.006
I think the baby ain't gone.

330
00:30:06.140 --> 00:30:08.975
I think the baby got plans.

331
00:30:11.978 --> 00:30:13.888
- Maybe.
- ♪ I know your house ♪♪

332
00:30:15.482 --> 00:30:17.356
[ Sethe ] Maybe so.

333
00:30:22.322 --> 00:30:25.192
[ Bird Squawking.
Wings Fluttering ]

334
00:30:25.325 --> 00:30:29.108
[ Snoring ]

335
00:30:29.245 --> 00:30:31.285
[ Wheezing ]

336
00:30:36.836 --> 00:30:41.581
[ Snoring. Wheezing Continue ]

337
00:30:44.969 --> 00:30:46.926
[ Gasping ]

338
00:31:08.032 --> 00:31:09.941
[ Wheezing Continues ]

339
00:31:16.457 --> 00:31:19.624
[ Snoring ]

340
00:31:40.230 --> 00:31:43.147
[ Wheezing. Snorting ]

341
00:31:53.201 --> 00:31:54.329
♪♪ [ Calliope ]

342
00:31:54.353 --> 00:31:58.021
[ Man ] Come one. come forward.
come all! Do not fear!

343
00:31:58.046 --> 00:32:03.038
Come inside to the largest lady.
Roundella. with me today.

344
00:32:03.120 --> 00:32:07.367
Sweet. gentle and delicate.
eating a chicken from each hand.

345
00:32:07.392 --> 00:32:11.388
Come inside now and see her.
Don't be afraid. Come this way.

346
00:32:11.412 --> 00:32:12.380
Wait! Come back!

347
00:32:12.405 --> 00:32:14.279
[ Crowd Chattering ]

348
00:32:18.100 --> 00:32:20.673
...and who will swallow
a Confederate sword to the hilt...

349
00:32:20.769 --> 00:32:22.892
in front of your very eyes.

350
00:32:22.979 --> 00:32:26.229
- Step forward and see!
- Whoo!

351
00:32:26.316 --> 00:32:29.436
[ Chattering ]

352
00:32:29.576 --> 00:32:31.699
Oh. Grace.

353
00:32:31.779 --> 00:32:34.161
You'll never believe
who come walkin' up in here.

354
00:32:34.185 --> 00:32:35.301
[ Lion Growling ]

355
00:32:35.325 --> 00:32:38.610
- How do?
- [ Man ] Come on. Lucy.

356
00:32:39.935 --> 00:32:41.890
[ Boy ]
Don't forget the pig ride.

357
00:32:41.915 --> 00:32:43.746
[ Paul D ]
How do. ma'am?

358
00:32:43.874 --> 00:32:47.742
[ Crowd Gasping. Applauding ]

359
00:32:47.878 --> 00:32:51.923
Step inside to see
the things you thought could never be.

360
00:32:52.007 --> 00:32:55.091
The ferocious African savage.
Cluck Butoo!

361
00:32:55.177 --> 00:32:59.590
Born with fangs. raised by wild animals
and captured crazy.

362
00:33:05.437 --> 00:33:07.762
Look how fat she is. Mama.

363
00:33:07.856 --> 00:33:09.765
[ Growling ]

364
00:33:13.903 --> 00:33:16.275
I-I knew this one
back in Roanoke.

365
00:33:20.410 --> 00:33:24.277
- Want some licorice. Denver?
- Yes. please.

366
00:33:24.372 --> 00:33:26.578
- Peppermint stick?
- Yes. please.

367
00:33:26.666 --> 00:33:30.200
- Some gumdrops?
- Yes. please.

368
00:33:33.493 --> 00:33:35.402
Mind if I take a sip?

369
00:33:45.726 --> 00:33:49.094
Mmm. Mmm!

370
00:33:52.983 --> 00:33:55.734
Hey. Denver!

371
00:33:55.860 --> 00:33:58.434
Hi.

372
00:33:59.140 --> 00:34:01.058
Thank you.

373
00:34:05.054 --> 00:34:07.282
I'll take
one of those lemonades too.

374
00:34:12.968 --> 00:34:14.535
But tell me about some work.

375
00:34:14.670 --> 00:34:16.304
I mean. tell me about
where I can find some.

376
00:34:16.328 --> 00:34:17.597
Well. they have--

377
00:34:19.057 --> 00:34:21.756
[ Man ]...turns his head
inside his own face...

378
00:34:21.885 --> 00:34:24.459
- and pulls his ears--
- [ Men Chattering ]

379
00:34:25.597 --> 00:34:28.847
[ Crowd Singing ]
♪ Headin' back ♪

380
00:34:28.975 --> 00:34:32.593
♪ Goin' home ♪

381
00:34:32.729 --> 00:34:35.765
♪♪ [ Continues ]

382
00:34:35.790 --> 00:34:39.075
[ Chattering ]

383
00:34:39.703 --> 00:34:41.477
What's that?

384
00:34:42.455 --> 00:34:45.231
♪ Ain't wanna hurt nobody ♪

385
00:34:45.366 --> 00:34:48.367
- ♪ Oh. no ♪
- [ Snoring ]

386
00:34:48.452 --> 00:34:50.860
♪ Ain't gonna hurt nobody ♪

387
00:34:50.955 --> 00:34:55.415
♪ Oh. Lord ♪

388
00:34:55.543 --> 00:34:57.369
♪♪ [ Continues ]

389
00:34:59.633 --> 00:35:00.960
[ Gasping ]

390
00:35:13.435 --> 00:35:15.308
Excuse me.

391
00:35:49.052 --> 00:35:50.961
[ Coughing ]

392
00:35:50.986 --> 00:35:53.524
You from around here?

393
00:36:09.864 --> 00:36:12.070
What might your name be?

394
00:36:12.200 --> 00:36:16.244
[ Speaking In Guttural Voice ]
B...

395
00:36:16.370 --> 00:36:18.992
E...

396
00:36:19.081 --> 00:36:21.370
L...

397
00:36:21.500 --> 00:36:22.994
O...

398
00:36:23.085 --> 00:36:25.457
V...

399
00:36:25.546 --> 00:36:28.547
E...

400
00:36:28.674 --> 00:36:30.880
D.

401
00:36:31.564 --> 00:36:34.627
Beloved. [ Grunting ]

402
00:36:36.473 --> 00:36:39.474
That's a pretty name. Beloved.

403
00:36:39.552 --> 00:36:43.100
Why don't you rest yourself while I--
I fix us a little somethin'.

404
00:36:43.132 --> 00:36:47.315
We just got back from the carnival
over in Cincinnati.

405
00:36:47.872 --> 00:36:51.398
[ Paul D ] Miss? Miss?

406
00:36:51.793 --> 00:36:53.735
You wanna rest a spell?

407
00:37:00.986 --> 00:37:03.144
- [ Beloved Gasping ]
- I got her!

408
00:37:03.541 --> 00:37:05.699
I got her. I got her.

409
00:37:09.254 --> 00:37:11.128
[ Whimpering ]

410
00:37:25.202 --> 00:37:26.717
Look at her feet.

411
00:37:27.822 --> 00:37:29.220
Ain't walkin' feet.

412
00:37:30.942 --> 00:37:32.933
- More like she...
- [ Wheezing ]

413
00:37:33.069 --> 00:37:34.943
ride from somewhere
all the way here.

414
00:37:35.545 --> 00:37:37.526
Is she feverish. Denver?

415
00:37:39.242 --> 00:37:41.364
No. she cold.

416
00:37:41.452 --> 00:37:45.035
- [ Paul D ] Could have the cholera.
- She ain't sick.

417
00:38:01.529 --> 00:38:02.559
[ Paul D Chuckling ]

418
00:38:02.584 --> 00:38:04.812
[ Sethe ] Nah. it's just
a little somethin' I whipped up.

419
00:38:04.837 --> 00:38:07.006
A little somethin'
you whipped up?

420
00:38:07.143 --> 00:38:09.599
- Mmm. Mmm.
- [ Beloved Moaning ]

421
00:38:13.233 --> 00:38:15.439
Heard there's work
down in Bucktown.

422
00:38:16.819 --> 00:38:19.108
Go see it for myself today.

423
00:38:26.120 --> 00:38:28.029
[ Paul D And Sethe Laughing ]

424
00:38:38.340 --> 00:38:40.214
[ Wheezing ]

425
00:38:43.512 --> 00:38:47.461
[ Snoring ]

426
00:38:55.690 --> 00:38:58.181
Mmm-mm.

427
00:38:58.318 --> 00:39:02.149
[ Paul D ]
Whoa! Whoa! Hey! Ho-ho! Whoa!

428
00:39:02.750 --> 00:39:03.940
Hey!

429
00:39:04.031 --> 00:39:05.940
[ Chattering ]

430
00:39:09.286 --> 00:39:11.658
[ Wheezing. Snoring Continue ]

431
00:39:39.857 --> 00:39:43.418
♪♪ [ Denver Singing ]

432
00:39:46.489 --> 00:39:48.861
- ♪♪ [ Stops ]
- [ Wheezing. Snoring Continue ]

433
00:40:05.257 --> 00:40:07.166
[ Grunting ]

434
00:40:24.025 --> 00:40:26.101
You wanna try some?

435
00:40:42.709 --> 00:40:45.247
Come on. come on.
Come on.

436
00:40:46.463 --> 00:40:49.168
- Over here. Come on.
- [ Beloved Wheezing ]

437
00:40:49.299 --> 00:40:51.173
There you go.

438
00:40:56.640 --> 00:40:59.095
Come on! [ Laughing ]

439
00:40:59.225 --> 00:41:03.638
I knew you could do it.
[ Chuckling ] Oh.

440
00:41:11.404 --> 00:41:13.277
You hungry?

441
00:41:16.992 --> 00:41:18.866
[ Giggles ]

442
00:41:31.447 --> 00:41:33.003
It's good!

443
00:41:36.845 --> 00:41:38.754
[ Giggling ]

444
00:41:42.851 --> 00:41:44.760
Slow down.

445
00:42:02.203 --> 00:42:04.112
[ Laughing ]

446
00:42:04.204 --> 00:42:06.660
♪♪ [ Woman Vocalizing ]

447
00:42:21.012 --> 00:42:22.886
Come on.

448
00:42:27.227 --> 00:42:30.477
Chicken. chicken.
shoo. shoo. shoo.

449
00:42:30.563 --> 00:42:34.886
- ♪♪ [ Vocalizing Stops ]
- I call this one June...

450
00:42:35.527 --> 00:42:37.567
and that's May.

451
00:42:39.766 --> 00:42:42.027
You gotta do soft touch.

452
00:42:42.158 --> 00:42:45.028
Remember?
Can you do soft touch?

453
00:42:45.160 --> 00:42:47.319
Touch it-- No!

454
00:42:47.479 --> 00:42:49.388
Beloved.

455
00:44:23.797 --> 00:44:26.169
[ Wheezing ]

456
00:44:26.558 --> 00:44:28.432
Beloved.

457
00:44:29.696 --> 00:44:32.946
I help make you bread.

458
00:44:34.724 --> 00:44:36.633
That's nice.

459
00:44:36.726 --> 00:44:38.635
Is my apron here?

460
00:44:40.313 --> 00:44:42.389
All right. we need a little flour.
We need some--

461
00:44:42.523 --> 00:44:45.310
I don't know.
I see you got all my things laid out.

462
00:44:45.335 --> 00:44:48.834
Oh. wait. wait. wait. wait.
Now you need some of that right there.

463
00:44:49.029 --> 00:44:51.188
You need this.

464
00:44:51.323 --> 00:44:54.075
There. Wait. wait.

465
00:44:54.201 --> 00:44:57.652
[ Paul D ]
♪ Little rice. little bean ♪

466
00:44:57.788 --> 00:45:00.741
♪ Ain't no meat in between ♪♪

467
00:45:00.766 --> 00:45:02.392
[ Beloved Chattering ]

468
00:45:02.417 --> 00:45:08.004
[ Denver Laughing ]
Ooh. look at you.

469
00:45:08.089 --> 00:45:10.794
Okay. put it down.
Put it back.

470
00:45:10.884 --> 00:45:12.793
♪♪ [ Continues ]

471
00:45:12.886 --> 00:45:16.420
[ Beloved ]
Go inside and get biscuit.

472
00:45:16.556 --> 00:45:18.762
Easy.

473
00:45:18.892 --> 00:45:22.177
[ Denver ]
♪ I went downtown to get my grits ♪

474
00:45:22.311 --> 00:45:25.478
♪ Came back home
just a-pullin' the skiff ♪

475
00:45:25.565 --> 00:45:27.937
♪ Just a-pullin' the skiff ♪

476
00:45:28.067 --> 00:45:31.103
♪ I ran upstairs
to make my bed ♪

477
00:45:31.237 --> 00:45:34.191
♪ I made a mistake
and I bumped my head ♪

478
00:45:34.281 --> 00:45:37.733
♪ Just a-pullin' the skiff
Just a-pullin' the skiff ♪

479
00:45:37.868 --> 00:45:41.237
♪ Went downstairs
to milk my cow ♪

480
00:45:41.371 --> 00:45:44.041
♪ I made a mistake
and I milked my sow ♪

481
00:45:44.066 --> 00:45:47.269
♪ Just a-pullin' the skiff
Just a-pullin' the skiff ♪

482
00:45:47.461 --> 00:45:50.711
♪ Tomorrow. tomorrow
Tomorrow never comes ♪

483
00:45:50.839 --> 00:45:53.959
♪ Tomorrow. tomorrow
Tomorrow never comes ♪♪

484
00:45:54.092 --> 00:45:57.212
♪♪ [ Singing ]

485
00:46:18.032 --> 00:46:20.902
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

486
00:46:23.537 --> 00:46:26.158
- [ Beloved Whimpering ]
- Come on!

487
00:46:26.290 --> 00:46:28.290
Clouds look like
they're gonna burst.

488
00:46:28.315 --> 00:46:30.604
- [ All Screaming. Laughing ]
- Oh. here it come!

489
00:46:30.877 --> 00:46:32.354
- Here. here!
- Come on. girl.

490
00:46:32.379 --> 00:46:35.166
- Here. Mama! Pull!
- Pull it!

491
00:46:35.298 --> 00:46:36.942
- Go! Go! Hurry up!
- Hurry up. Come on.

492
00:46:36.967 --> 00:46:39.374
- Beloved. pick up that sheet.
- Run! It's raining!

493
00:46:39.469 --> 00:46:41.794
- You're draggin' it on the ground.
- Go!

494
00:46:41.930 --> 00:46:44.385
[ Screaming. Laughing Continue ]

495
00:46:48.352 --> 00:46:51.104
Stop draggin' them sheets.
Pick 'em up off the ground now...

496
00:46:51.129 --> 00:46:53.667
so we don't have
to wash 'em again.

497
00:46:53.899 --> 00:46:56.022
Come on. Whoo!

498
00:46:56.152 --> 00:46:58.856
Almost didn't make it.

499
00:46:58.988 --> 00:47:01.664
Spread 'em out.
Beloved. put that sheet down now.

500
00:47:01.689 --> 00:47:03.899
Spread it out.
Keep it up off the floor.

501
00:47:05.160 --> 00:47:07.069
♪♪ [ Singing ]

502
00:47:51.788 --> 00:47:53.698
Where...

503
00:47:53.832 --> 00:47:56.916
you diamonds?

504
00:47:58.462 --> 00:48:01.166
Diamonds? [ Chuckles ]

505
00:48:01.298 --> 00:48:03.871
What would I be doin'
with diamonds?

506
00:48:04.340 --> 00:48:07.424
On you ears.

507
00:48:10.390 --> 00:48:12.299
Wish I did.

508
00:48:13.601 --> 00:48:16.970
Come to think of it...

509
00:48:17.063 --> 00:48:20.396
I had some crystal once.

510
00:48:20.524 --> 00:48:22.896
Present from the lady
I used to work for.

511
00:48:23.400 --> 00:48:24.900
Tell me.

512
00:48:26.905 --> 00:48:29.527
Tell me you diamonds.

513
00:48:29.616 --> 00:48:32.368
Wedding present
from Miss Garner...

514
00:48:32.452 --> 00:48:35.122
back at Sweet Home...

515
00:48:35.247 --> 00:48:40.074
when Halle and me got married-- what
they called married back there and then.

516
00:48:40.210 --> 00:48:43.875
Guess she saw how bad
I felt when...

517
00:48:43.964 --> 00:48:47.048
I saw there wasn't gonna be
no ceremony. no preacher.

518
00:48:48.343 --> 00:48:52.043
I never saw you
with no crystals.

519
00:48:52.138 --> 00:48:54.807
Gone.

520
00:48:54.932 --> 00:48:56.806
Long gone.

521
00:49:00.771 --> 00:49:03.974
Come here. girl.
You best unbraid that hair.

522
00:49:05.109 --> 00:49:06.983
Come on.
Get the comb.

523
00:49:09.613 --> 00:49:11.189
It's right here.

524
00:49:12.950 --> 00:49:14.989
Ow! That hurts.

525
00:49:15.118 --> 00:49:18.404
Comb it every day. it won't.

526
00:49:18.497 --> 00:49:20.703
You woman...

527
00:49:20.791 --> 00:49:25.084
never fix up you hair?

528
00:49:25.170 --> 00:49:27.625
My woman?
You mean my mother?

529
00:49:27.756 --> 00:49:31.006
Mama don't talk about
all those things.

530
00:49:31.134 --> 00:49:33.008
Tell me.

531
00:49:36.889 --> 00:49:39.096
If she did. I don't remember.

532
00:49:39.225 --> 00:49:42.973
I don't think I saw her
but a few times out in the field...

533
00:49:43.104 --> 00:49:45.476
once workin' indigo.

534
00:49:46.982 --> 00:49:52.225
By the time I woke up mornings.
she was in line.

535
00:49:52.321 --> 00:49:55.904
Hmm. If the moon was bright.
they worked by its light.

536
00:49:55.991 --> 00:50:00.285
Sundays. she slept like a stick.

537
00:50:02.039 --> 00:50:05.242
Tell me about her.

538
00:50:08.336 --> 00:50:13.710
I remember. once. she picked me up
and carried me behind the smokehouse.

539
00:50:14.843 --> 00:50:17.713
Only thing I do remember.
in fact.

540
00:50:19.681 --> 00:50:24.805
She opened up her dress.
and right on her rib--

541
00:50:24.894 --> 00:50:26.803
right here--

542
00:50:29.857 --> 00:50:32.063
was a circle...

543
00:50:32.193 --> 00:50:36.060
and a cross
burnt right in the skin.

544
00:50:36.196 --> 00:50:39.446
She points at this mark.
and she says--

545
00:50:39.533 --> 00:50:41.656
she says to me...

546
00:50:41.743 --> 00:50:46.986
"This is your ma'am.
I'm the only one got this mark now.

547
00:50:47.082 --> 00:50:49.205
The rest all dead.

548
00:50:49.673 --> 00:50:52.204
Somethin' happen to me.
you can't tell me by my face...

549
00:50:52.229 --> 00:50:55.395
you know me by this mark."

550
00:50:55.590 --> 00:50:57.614
Scared me so I couldn't think
of nothin' to say...

551
00:50:57.639 --> 00:51:00.670
so I says. "Yes. ma'am.

552
00:51:00.803 --> 00:51:03.555
But how you know me?
Mark the mark on me.

553
00:51:03.681 --> 00:51:05.839
Mark me too."

554
00:51:05.933 --> 00:51:08.222
Did she?

555
00:51:08.686 --> 00:51:10.226
No.

556
00:51:10.354 --> 00:51:13.106
She slapped my face.

557
00:51:16.860 --> 00:51:19.233
I didn't understand it then.

558
00:51:21.573 --> 00:51:24.491
Not till I had a mark of my own.

559
00:51:25.953 --> 00:51:30.863
[ Beloved ]
What happened to her?

560
00:51:30.999 --> 00:51:33.668
Hung.

561
00:51:37.505 --> 00:51:41.882
Ma'am. What's the matter
with you. ma'am?

562
00:51:45.263 --> 00:51:46.721
Why they hang your mama?

563
00:51:48.933 --> 00:51:51.554
I never found out.

564
00:51:53.104 --> 00:51:55.013
Was a lot of 'em.

565
00:51:55.106 --> 00:51:57.228
[ People Crying ]

566
00:51:57.358 --> 00:51:59.730
- [ Bones Cracking ]
- [ Woman Sobbing ]

567
00:52:46.405 --> 00:52:49.240
Paul D be here in a minute.

568
00:52:59.209 --> 00:53:01.616
Hope this pudding's
good tonight.

569
00:53:04.547 --> 00:53:06.955
Denver. pass me
your plate down here.

570
00:53:11.012 --> 00:53:12.885
Paul D.

571
00:53:35.180 --> 00:53:38.793
Where you been all them years...

572
00:53:38.818 --> 00:53:42.234
since Sweet Home. Mr Paul?

573
00:53:42.328 --> 00:53:44.736
Ain't you got no people?

574
00:53:45.305 --> 00:53:48.164
- You wanna know about me now.
- Uh-huh.

575
00:53:55.816 --> 00:53:57.628
I got no people.

576
00:54:03.395 --> 00:54:07.773
Eighteen years since I left Sweet Home.
and I've been walkin' the whole time.

577
00:54:07.900 --> 00:54:12.608
Move. walk. run. hide.
sometimes steal and move on.

578
00:54:15.001 --> 00:54:18.364
Only time I stayed in one spot
for more than a month or so...

579
00:54:18.446 --> 00:54:21.068
was with a weaver woman
in Wilmington. Delaware.

580
00:54:21.246 --> 00:54:23.653
Meanest place for a Negro
I ever seen...

581
00:54:23.748 --> 00:54:26.702
outside of Pulaski County.
Kentucky.

582
00:54:27.473 --> 00:54:31.371
I seen Negroes
so stunned and hungry...

583
00:54:31.464 --> 00:54:34.299
they lived in caves and
fought owls for food.

584
00:54:34.425 --> 00:54:36.714
Seen some who slept
in trees in the day...

585
00:54:36.739 --> 00:54:38.593
and moved only by night...

586
00:54:38.721 --> 00:54:42.172
who buried themselves in slop
to hide from...

587
00:54:42.266 --> 00:54:45.931
posses and lawmen
and regulators.

588
00:54:46.061 --> 00:54:49.228
Met a Negro boy once--
about 14--

589
00:54:49.433 --> 00:54:51.652
- who lived by hisself in the woods...
- [ Sighing ]

590
00:54:51.677 --> 00:54:55.010
and said he could never remember
livin' anywhere else.

591
00:54:55.709 --> 00:54:58.897
Seen a witless
colored woman hang...

592
00:54:59.463 --> 00:55:02.324
for stealing ducks
she believed was her own babies.

593
00:55:06.581 --> 00:55:09.748
In all these years. girl...

594
00:55:09.876 --> 00:55:12.581
you beat all.

595
00:55:12.670 --> 00:55:15.588
I ain't never seen
a Negro like you.

596
00:55:18.384 --> 00:55:21.670
I think it's time you tell us
a little somethin' about yourself.

597
00:55:21.804 --> 00:55:23.678
She don't remember nothin'.

598
00:55:23.806 --> 00:55:27.969
Oh. you'd be surprised what you start
rememberin' soon as you start talkin'.

599
00:55:30.463 --> 00:55:33.599
Ain't you got
no brothers or sisters?

600
00:55:38.320 --> 00:55:42.020
I ain't got nobody.

601
00:55:42.157 --> 00:55:44.031
Paul D. stop it.

602
00:55:45.452 --> 00:55:48.287
Denver. help me
clean up this table.

603
00:55:48.371 --> 00:55:50.779
I wanna know. Sethe.

604
00:55:54.335 --> 00:55:57.396
What you lookin' for
when you come here. Beloved?

605
00:56:00.012 --> 00:56:01.886
This place.

606
00:56:04.220 --> 00:56:07.885
I look for this place
I could be in.

607
00:56:08.015 --> 00:56:10.091
Somebody tell you
about this place?

608
00:56:16.523 --> 00:56:18.432
She told me.

609
00:56:19.860 --> 00:56:24.901
When I was at the bridge.
she told me.

610
00:56:25.032 --> 00:56:27.867
How you come? Who brung ya?

611
00:56:30.036 --> 00:56:31.945
I walk here.

612
00:56:35.041 --> 00:56:39.454
It's a long. long.
long. long way.

613
00:56:40.964 --> 00:56:44.582
- Nobody bring me.
- You wearin' new shoes. gal.

614
00:56:44.717 --> 00:56:47.080
If you walked so long. how come
your shoes don't show it?

615
00:56:47.198 --> 00:56:48.240
[ Sethe ] Paul D.

616
00:56:48.427 --> 00:56:49.720
Stop pickin' on her.

617
00:56:49.847 --> 00:56:53.547
I wanna know! Where you get
them shoes and the dress you had on?

618
00:56:53.684 --> 00:56:57.634
I take the shoes.
and I take the dress!

619
00:56:59.064 --> 00:57:02.729
The shoestrings don't fit.

620
00:57:02.860 --> 00:57:05.730
I'll teach you
how to tie your shoes.

621
00:57:08.193 --> 00:57:10.066
[ Gagging ]

622
00:57:14.121 --> 00:57:16.497
Beloved. Beloved!

623
00:57:17.791 --> 00:57:19.368
- [ Coughing ]
- Beloved.

624
00:57:19.565 --> 00:57:22.186
Beloved. Beloved. you all right?

625
00:57:22.211 --> 00:57:24.085
- Let it out.
- [ Hand Hitting Back ]

626
00:57:24.213 --> 00:57:26.455
Go to sleep now.

627
00:57:26.591 --> 00:57:29.378
[ Denver ]
You can come in my room.

628
00:57:29.468 --> 00:57:31.876
I can take care of you up there.

629
00:57:34.265 --> 00:57:36.637
[ Crying Continues ]

630
00:57:42.272 --> 00:57:45.641
What's the matter with you?
What is it about her vex you so?

631
00:57:45.776 --> 00:57:48.397
I don't understand
what the hold is.

632
00:57:48.487 --> 00:57:52.864
It's clear why she hold on to you. I
just can't see why you holdin' on to her.

633
00:57:52.949 --> 00:57:55.701
What you care
who holdin' on to who?

634
00:57:55.785 --> 00:57:58.241
She nice girl.
company for Denver.

635
00:57:58.330 --> 00:58:00.239
There's something funny
about that gal.

636
00:58:00.331 --> 00:58:02.822
Act sick. sound sick.
but she don't look sick.

637
00:58:03.146 --> 00:58:05.580
Eats sweets all day long.
as strong as a bull.

638
00:58:05.670 --> 00:58:09.714
She not strong. She can't hardly even
walk without holdin' on to somethin'.

639
00:58:09.799 --> 00:58:12.468
Can't walk. but I seen her pick up
the rocker with one hand.

640
00:58:12.593 --> 00:58:14.467
You ain't seen no such a-thing.

641
00:58:14.595 --> 00:58:17.596
Hey. don't tell me. Ask Denver.
She right there with her.

642
00:58:19.350 --> 00:58:23.762
Sethe. Sethe. baby.

643
00:58:23.854 --> 00:58:28.571
We were startin' to feel a little like
a family ourself till she come along.

644
00:58:28.596 --> 00:58:32.351
- Is that what got your teeth on edge?
- It's a feelin' in me.

645
00:58:32.487 --> 00:58:36.615
- I can't place it. It's her.
- You wanna feel somethin'?

646
00:58:37.057 --> 00:58:40.234
Feel what it feel like to be
a colored woman roamin' the roads.

647
00:58:40.328 --> 00:58:43.578
And anything God made
liable to jump on you. Feel that!

648
00:58:43.870 --> 00:58:45.788
I know every bit of that. Sethe.

649
00:58:45.813 --> 00:58:48.478
I wasn't born yesterday. and I never
mistreated a woman in my life.

650
00:58:48.503 --> 00:58:51.373
Well. that makes
one of you in this world.

651
00:58:51.506 --> 00:58:53.878
One. Not two?

652
00:58:57.678 --> 00:58:59.552
No. not two.

653
00:59:01.765 --> 00:59:04.553
What'd Halle ever do to you?
Halle stood by you.

654
00:59:04.870 --> 00:59:07.888
Halle ran off.

655
00:59:08.021 --> 00:59:11.390
He left me.
and he left our children.

656
00:59:11.525 --> 00:59:14.479
- You don't know that.
- Who he leave then if he didn't leave me?

657
00:59:14.569 --> 00:59:17.985
He wasn't there.
He wasn't where he said he was gonna be.

658
00:59:18.073 --> 00:59:20.646
I had to pack my babies off
ahead of me on their own.

659
00:59:20.742 --> 00:59:22.651
Stayed behind to look for him.

660
00:59:22.744 --> 00:59:26.077
Got caught by Schoolteacher
and his boys for my trouble.

661
00:59:26.206 --> 00:59:28.079
[ Dishes Clattering ]

662
00:59:32.818 --> 00:59:36.103
He couldn't get out
the... loft. I expect.

663
00:59:39.743 --> 00:59:41.336
Loft?

664
00:59:41.912 --> 00:59:43.505
What loft?

665
00:59:43.597 --> 00:59:46.005
One in the barn. I reckon.

666
00:59:51.438 --> 00:59:53.347
He was there?

667
00:59:55.486 --> 00:59:57.728
How do you know?

668
01:00:00.822 --> 01:00:02.696
Mornin' after you run.
I seen Halle...

669
01:00:02.824 --> 01:00:04.698
chained to a post.

670
01:00:05.910 --> 01:00:09.114
I said. "What happened?
Where you been?"

671
01:00:09.247 --> 01:00:12.865
"The loft. the loft. The loft."

672
01:00:12.959 --> 01:00:15.201
That's all he said.

673
01:00:15.336 --> 01:00:19.416
- Could never figure out what he meant by that.
- [ Sighing ]

674
01:00:23.427 --> 01:00:26.713
He saw them boys do that to me?

675
01:00:27.848 --> 01:00:30.635
And he let them
keep on breathin'?

676
01:00:31.336 --> 01:00:33.768
I-I ask him...

677
01:00:33.896 --> 01:00:35.805
"How come you didn't run
with Sethe?"

678
01:00:35.939 --> 01:00:37.896
He never answered me.

679
01:00:37.983 --> 01:00:42.312
I seen him once more. the day
Schoolteacher sold me to Brandywine.

680
01:00:42.446 --> 01:00:45.316
Takin' me away in the wagon.

681
01:00:45.448 --> 01:00:48.022
There Halle was. in the yard...

682
01:00:48.118 --> 01:00:50.406
sittin' by the churn.

683
01:00:52.622 --> 01:00:58.043
They didn't need to put no chains on him
no more. His mind was gone.

684
01:01:06.208 --> 01:01:07.877
Sethe...

685
01:01:12.725 --> 01:01:16.058
a man ain't a goddam axe...

686
01:01:16.145 --> 01:01:18.386
choppin' and hackin'...

687
01:01:18.480 --> 01:01:21.730
bustin' every minute of the day.

688
01:01:21.817 --> 01:01:23.856
Things get to him.

689
01:01:23.985 --> 01:01:27.354
Things he can't chop down
'cause they inside.

690
01:01:29.190 --> 01:01:32.144
Halle never just run off
and leave you. Sethe.

691
01:01:33.078 --> 01:01:35.913
You see...

692
01:01:35.997 --> 01:01:39.829
you the only one of us
who made it out that night.

693
01:01:40.488 --> 01:01:42.331
The only one.

694
01:02:13.533 --> 01:02:15.407
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

695
01:02:20.206 --> 01:02:23.124
I didn't plan
on telling you all that.

696
01:02:27.230 --> 01:02:29.002
I'm sorry.

697
01:02:31.675 --> 01:02:34.048
I didn't plan on hearin' it.

698
01:02:36.972 --> 01:02:40.637
Didn't plan on you
walkin' down that road neither...

699
01:02:40.726 --> 01:02:43.264
comin' into my house...

700
01:02:43.395 --> 01:02:45.767
bringin' all this with you.

701
01:02:54.155 --> 01:02:55.698
[ Denver Humming ]

702
01:02:58.368 --> 01:03:00.241
[ Denver Giggling ]

703
01:03:04.040 --> 01:03:07.954
- Where'd you learn to dance?
- Nowhere!

704
01:03:08.085 --> 01:03:10.493
Watch me do this.

705
01:03:10.588 --> 01:03:12.497
Ohh!

706
01:03:12.590 --> 01:03:15.211
[ Laughing ]
Now you! Come on!

707
01:03:15.236 --> 01:03:18.190
You may as well.
Just go on!

708
01:03:18.387 --> 01:03:20.261
[ Laughing ]

709
01:03:20.389 --> 01:03:22.761
[ Screaming ]

710
01:03:26.520 --> 01:03:28.892
[ Groaning. Sighing ]

711
01:03:39.449 --> 01:03:42.070
Why you call yourself Beloved?

712
01:03:44.162 --> 01:03:48.954
In the dark. my name Beloved.

713
01:03:49.083 --> 01:03:54.078
What's it like where you was before?
Can you tell me?

714
01:03:54.213 --> 01:03:58.590
Dark. I was small
in that place...

715
01:03:59.677 --> 01:04:02.250
like this here.

716
01:04:02.346 --> 01:04:05.133
- Were you cold?
- Hot!

717
01:04:05.265 --> 01:04:08.603
Nothing to breathe down there.

718
01:04:08.628 --> 01:04:13.206
No room to move.

719
01:04:16.193 --> 01:04:18.102
You see anybody?

720
01:04:19.446 --> 01:04:21.604
It's a lot of people...

721
01:04:21.698 --> 01:04:23.607
down there.

722
01:04:24.868 --> 01:04:27.109
Some is dead.

723
01:04:27.623 --> 01:04:31.616
You see Jesus? Baby Suggs?

724
01:04:32.792 --> 01:04:35.828
I don't know.

725
01:04:35.853 --> 01:04:38.094
I don't know the names.

726
01:04:39.507 --> 01:04:42.377
Well. what you
come back here for?

727
01:04:44.887 --> 01:04:48.469
To see her face.

728
01:04:48.599 --> 01:04:50.722
Mama's?

729
01:04:50.851 --> 01:04:52.974
Sethe's?

730
01:04:53.061 --> 01:04:55.896
Sethe.

731
01:04:57.034 --> 01:04:58.826
I remember!

732
01:05:00.360 --> 01:05:02.234
I remember!

733
01:05:02.362 --> 01:05:04.983
I was in the water.

734
01:05:05.318 --> 01:05:09.117
I see her diamonds down there.

735
01:05:13.706 --> 01:05:16.992
Then she left me behind...

736
01:05:17.084 --> 01:05:20.085
by myself.

737
01:05:23.382 --> 01:05:25.256
Don't.

738
01:05:26.385 --> 01:05:29.801
You won't ever leave us.
will ya?

739
01:05:31.932 --> 01:05:35.680
No. Never.

740
01:05:35.769 --> 01:05:38.723
This is where I am!

741
01:05:41.608 --> 01:05:43.517
Don't tell.

742
01:05:43.610 --> 01:05:46.734
Please don't let Mama know who you are.
You hear me?

743
01:05:46.759 --> 01:05:48.445
Don't tell me what to do!

744
01:05:48.573 --> 01:05:51.776
Don't you never. never
tell me what to do!

745
01:05:51.910 --> 01:05:54.198
- But I'm on your side!
- She the one!

746
01:05:54.287 --> 01:05:56.196
She the one I need!

747
01:05:56.289 --> 01:06:01.200
You can go!
She the one I have to have!

748
01:06:25.609 --> 01:06:28.360
[ Mumbles ]

749
01:06:37.286 --> 01:06:40.157
Tell me how Sethe...

750
01:06:40.289 --> 01:06:42.994
make you in the boat.

751
01:06:47.921 --> 01:06:49.756
Tell me.

752
01:06:53.010 --> 01:06:55.797
She never told me all of it.

753
01:06:57.806 --> 01:06:59.715
Tell me.

754
01:07:01.810 --> 01:07:03.719
Denver.

755
01:07:05.522 --> 01:07:08.770
Tell me. [ Crying ]

756
01:07:11.903 --> 01:07:13.777
Well--

757
01:07:15.657 --> 01:07:18.618
Mama was runnin'!

758
01:07:18.743 --> 01:07:21.032
- [ Bird Squawking ]
- [ Sethe Panting ]

759
01:07:28.502 --> 01:07:30.459
[ Screaming ]

760
01:07:35.634 --> 01:07:38.588
[ Moaning ]

761
01:07:44.184 --> 01:07:47.470
[ Moaning Continues ]

762
01:07:47.939 --> 01:07:49.478
Who in there?

763
01:07:50.941 --> 01:07:53.313
Who that back there?

764
01:07:56.237 --> 01:07:58.645
[ Panting ]

765
01:07:58.740 --> 01:08:02.415
[ Chuckling ] My. my. my.

766
01:08:02.440 --> 01:08:04.193
My. my. my. my!

767
01:08:04.328 --> 01:08:07.911
It's a nigger!
If that don't beat all!

768
01:08:09.455 --> 01:08:12.519
Girl. you about the scariest-lookin'
somethin' I ever saw.

769
01:08:12.778 --> 01:08:14.688
What you doin' way back up here?

770
01:08:15.891 --> 01:08:17.532
I'm runnin'.

771
01:08:19.051 --> 01:08:20.960
These the feet you runnin' on?

772
01:08:20.985 --> 01:08:23.273
- [ Groans ]
- Jesus. my!

773
01:08:23.430 --> 01:08:26.716
Miss. am I in Ohio?
[ Gasps ]

774
01:08:26.850 --> 01:08:29.970
[ Chuckling ] Ohio?
No. girl. you in Kentucky.

775
01:08:30.061 --> 01:08:32.350
You about a thousand miles
away from Ohio.

776
01:08:32.942 --> 01:08:34.764
You havin' a baby?

777
01:08:34.899 --> 01:08:36.773
Oh. my!

778
01:08:36.901 --> 01:08:40.317
I expect this baby there
is gonna die in these wild onions.

779
01:08:41.159 --> 01:08:42.978
I gotta eat me somethin'.

780
01:08:43.703 --> 01:08:47.321
W-W-Where-Where was you
on your way to-to. miss?

781
01:08:47.411 --> 01:08:50.247
Boston. Get me some velvet.

782
01:08:50.373 --> 01:08:54.619
It's a store called Wilson's.
They just have the "purtiest" velvet.

783
01:08:54.752 --> 01:08:56.958
You ever seen velvet
or touched it?

784
01:08:57.087 --> 01:09:00.254
I-if-- If I did.
I didn't know it.

785
01:09:01.137 --> 01:09:02.788
Velvet I seen was brown...

786
01:09:02.813 --> 01:09:05.510
but in Boston.
they got all colors.

787
01:09:07.894 --> 01:09:09.715
What they call you?

788
01:09:10.688 --> 01:09:12.299
L-Lu.

789
01:09:12.436 --> 01:09:14.891
[ Nervously Chuckling ]

790
01:09:15.021 --> 01:09:17.726
Well. what you gonna do. Lu?
You just gonna lay here and foal?

791
01:09:17.816 --> 01:09:22.276
I-- I-I can't get up.
I-I can't move.

792
01:09:22.403 --> 01:09:25.938
Oh. sure. you can. Lu. Come on.
You stay here. the snakes might get ya.

793
01:09:25.963 --> 01:09:27.872
- I can't.
- Come on. come on.

794
01:09:28.117 --> 01:09:31.901
- Come on. come on. Come on.
- [ Groaning ]

795
01:09:33.789 --> 01:09:36.115
Come on!

796
01:09:36.250 --> 01:09:40.746
I was fishin' off the Beaver once
when a nigger floated right by me.

797
01:09:40.838 --> 01:09:43.589
I don't like drowned people much.
Do you?

798
01:09:46.432 --> 01:09:48.423
Your feet kinda
reminded me of him.

799
01:09:48.851 --> 01:09:50.421
All swoll-like.

800
01:09:53.805 --> 01:09:55.758
- Now this is gonna hurt a little.
- [ Groaning ]

801
01:09:55.852 --> 01:09:57.925
Anything dead comin' back
to life hurts.

802
01:09:57.950 --> 01:10:01.864
You ain't got no business
pokin' 'round these hills. miss.

803
01:10:02.150 --> 01:10:04.273
Lookit here who's talkin'.

804
01:10:04.360 --> 01:10:06.838
Ain't nobody after me.
but I know somebody after you...

805
01:10:06.863 --> 01:10:09.947
and they catch you.
they gonna cut your head off.

806
01:10:10.033 --> 01:10:13.117
- Stop wiggling. girl.
- My back hurt me.

807
01:10:13.202 --> 01:10:15.111
- Your back?
- Yeah.

808
01:10:15.136 --> 01:10:18.671
Girl. you a mess.
Turn over here and let me see.

809
01:10:18.696 --> 01:10:20.605
[ Groaning ]

810
01:10:33.180 --> 01:10:35.552
[ Screaming. Moaning ]

811
01:10:36.683 --> 01:10:39.554
Come here. Jesus!

812
01:10:41.988 --> 01:10:44.396
It's a tree. Lu.

813
01:10:44.441 --> 01:10:47.014
Your back got
a whole tree on it.

814
01:10:47.152 --> 01:10:50.437
Chokecherry tree in bloom.

815
01:10:50.530 --> 01:10:52.818
See? Here's the trunk.

816
01:10:52.907 --> 01:10:58.411
It's spread and split wide open.
full of sap and branches.

817
01:10:58.537 --> 01:11:01.242
And darned if these ain't blossoms.

818
01:11:02.416 --> 01:11:05.334
Come on. girl. [ Gasping ]

819
01:11:07.212 --> 01:11:10.166
'Cause of me.
you're up and walkin'.

820
01:11:10.257 --> 01:11:13.258
See. Jesus.
Lu made it through.

821
01:11:13.385 --> 01:11:15.508
I'm good with sick things.
ain't I?

822
01:11:15.637 --> 01:11:17.511
Yeah. you good.

823
01:11:19.391 --> 01:11:22.594
- What's all over your dress. girl?
- It's milk.

824
01:11:22.727 --> 01:11:24.601
Gotta get milk to my baby girl.

825
01:11:24.626 --> 01:11:27.461
You mean. you got
another baby waitin' for you?

826
01:11:27.690 --> 01:11:29.564
Oh. my. Jesus.

827
01:11:33.404 --> 01:11:36.773
- [ Panting ]
- Come on.

828
01:11:46.208 --> 01:11:50.040
Come on. Come on.

829
01:11:51.714 --> 01:11:54.169
[ Giggling ] Now...

830
01:11:55.259 --> 01:11:58.010
that's Ohio.

831
01:12:24.120 --> 01:12:26.871
[ Giggling ]

832
01:12:34.463 --> 01:12:36.502
Jesus lookin' at you. girl!

833
01:12:36.632 --> 01:12:38.505
[ Laughing ]

834
01:12:39.740 --> 01:12:42.211
Whoo! Come on.

835
01:12:42.236 --> 01:12:45.054
[ Groaning ]

836
01:12:46.113 --> 01:12:49.469
Oh. here's your paddle!

837
01:12:54.107 --> 01:12:56.894
- [ Screaming ]
- What you doin' now. poor girl?

838
01:12:58.403 --> 01:13:00.617
- [ Gasping ]
- Stop that right now!

839
01:13:00.642 --> 01:13:04.361
- Jesus. Lu! Stop it! Stop it!
- [ Panting ]

840
01:13:04.492 --> 01:13:06.848
Lu! Lu! Stop it!

841
01:13:06.873 --> 01:13:09.957
Oh. Jesus! I'm awfully sorry
about braggin'.

842
01:13:10.331 --> 01:13:12.952
I need you here now!

843
01:13:13.042 --> 01:13:16.790
- Don't be gettin' lost on me now. Jesus!
- [ Continues Panting ]

844
01:13:16.879 --> 01:13:20.045
Come on! Push! Push!

845
01:13:20.174 --> 01:13:22.546
- [ Screaming ]
- Push!

846
01:13:22.676 --> 01:13:24.254
Oh. here comes the head.

847
01:13:24.344 --> 01:13:27.262
Oh. dear Jesus. please. help!

848
01:13:27.347 --> 01:13:29.387
God. it's stuck!

849
01:13:29.516 --> 01:13:33.216
- [ Grunting ] Come on!
- [ Screaming ]

850
01:13:33.353 --> 01:13:36.473
[ Panting ]

851
01:13:36.564 --> 01:13:38.771
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Baby Crying ]

852
01:13:46.282 --> 01:13:49.781
Oh. praise Jesus.
Praise Jesus.

853
01:13:49.869 --> 01:13:51.778
[ Crying Continues ]

854
01:14:04.633 --> 01:14:07.503
She ain't never
gonna know who I am.

855
01:14:11.139 --> 01:14:13.511
You better tell her who brung her
into this world.

856
01:14:13.642 --> 01:14:15.515
[ Crying ]

857
01:14:15.644 --> 01:14:19.558
You say. "Miss Amy Denver...

858
01:14:19.689 --> 01:14:22.061
- of Boston."
- Mm.

859
01:14:23.192 --> 01:14:26.561
Pretty. That's pretty.

860
01:14:28.030 --> 01:14:29.904
Denver.

861
01:14:31.033 --> 01:14:34.983
Real pretty. Shh.

862
01:14:37.414 --> 01:14:40.914
[ Denver Narrating ] So Amy Denver.
she left me and Mama on the riverbank.

863
01:14:41.043 --> 01:14:43.795
That was the first time
we met Stamp Paid.

864
01:14:46.089 --> 01:14:47.999
[ Denver Crying ]

865
01:15:11.674 --> 01:15:13.906
Hey there.

866
01:15:14.343 --> 01:15:15.907
You headin' across?

867
01:15:17.814 --> 01:15:20.186
Yes. sir.

868
01:15:20.725 --> 01:15:23.740
Anybody know you comin'?

869
01:15:25.127 --> 01:15:28.044
Yes. sir.
My mother-in-law. Baby Suggs.

870
01:15:29.381 --> 01:15:31.255
[ Crying Continues ]

871
01:15:59.285 --> 01:16:02.202
[ Denver Narrating ]
Most folk call her Baby Suggs Holy.

872
01:16:02.329 --> 01:16:06.457
- To me. she were Grandma Baby.
- [ Laughing ]

873
01:16:08.544 --> 01:16:11.959
Thank you. Ella.
Thank you. Stamp.

874
01:16:13.566 --> 01:16:15.986
[ Laughing ] Oh!

875
01:16:16.093 --> 01:16:19.960
[ Laughing Continues ]

876
01:16:20.096 --> 01:16:23.761
Oh. my Lord.

877
01:16:23.850 --> 01:16:26.602
My sweet Jesus!

878
01:16:26.686 --> 01:16:28.595
Thank you!

879
01:16:29.856 --> 01:16:33.225
- [ Baby Suggs Laughing ]
- [ Sethe Crying ]

880
01:16:33.312 --> 01:16:35.186
Where's my Halle?

881
01:16:35.361 --> 01:16:37.852
Well. he w-wasn't there...

882
01:16:37.962 --> 01:16:41.212
where he said to meet him.
and I had to go.

883
01:16:41.367 --> 01:16:43.241
Had to.

884
01:16:43.369 --> 01:16:45.278
H-H-He'll make it.

885
01:16:45.371 --> 01:16:48.325
If I made it. Halle sure can.

886
01:16:49.583 --> 01:16:53.331
- Where-Where's my children?
- Oh. no. not now.

887
01:16:53.462 --> 01:16:55.371
We got to fix you up first.

888
01:16:55.591 --> 01:16:59.210
You too ugly-lookin'
to wake 'em. [ Laughing ]

889
01:17:03.889 --> 01:17:07.257
- Shh.
- [ Door Opening ]

890
01:17:09.561 --> 01:17:12.811
- Buglar. Howard!
- [ Both ] Mama. Mama!

891
01:17:14.155 --> 01:17:17.441
- Oh. look at you.
- [ Children Laughing ]

892
01:17:17.735 --> 01:17:19.811
Let me see. Oh!

893
01:17:19.904 --> 01:17:22.311
Tell me the other baby.

894
01:17:22.406 --> 01:17:24.862
Tell me you big sister.

895
01:17:24.992 --> 01:17:27.697
[ Denver ]
Mm. Baby Suggs call her...

896
01:17:27.828 --> 01:17:31.695
Crawlin' Already Baby.

897
01:17:31.745 --> 01:17:36.168
Crawlin' already?
Ain't this somethin'?

898
01:17:36.193 --> 01:17:39.206
All right. baby girl.
Right this way.

899
01:17:39.298 --> 01:17:41.207
Mama's waitin'.

900
01:17:46.553 --> 01:17:48.552
All right. Howard. Buglar.

901
01:17:48.682 --> 01:17:50.555
[ Crying ]

902
01:17:53.895 --> 01:17:56.849
You're okay. Yeah.

903
01:17:56.939 --> 01:18:00.143
Ain't nothin' here worth savin'.

904
01:18:00.276 --> 01:18:03.692
What is this?

905
01:18:03.779 --> 01:18:06.307
Weddin' present from Mrs Garner.

906
01:18:08.284 --> 01:18:12.910
I wish there was a groom
to go with it.

907
01:18:21.129 --> 01:18:23.039
Put 'em on. child.

908
01:18:24.424 --> 01:18:29.086
Maybe they'll light his way.

909
01:18:31.473 --> 01:18:34.260
Look at those shine.

910
01:18:34.350 --> 01:18:36.260
Pretty. huh?

911
01:18:40.148 --> 01:18:42.769
Daddy come soon. huh?

912
01:18:45.319 --> 01:18:48.190
No matter what happen...

913
01:18:48.322 --> 01:18:51.406
God has led you home.

914
01:18:52.493 --> 01:18:54.402
So...

915
01:18:54.495 --> 01:18:56.950
Lay 'em down. Sethe.

916
01:18:57.039 --> 01:19:00.040
Sword and shield.

917
01:19:00.444 --> 01:19:02.788
Study war no more.

918
01:19:03.044 --> 01:19:05.240
God has led you home.

919
01:19:10.720 --> 01:19:14.338
- Where we goin'. Mama?
- We goin' to pay tribute to your daddy.

920
01:19:16.808 --> 01:19:19.381
Our house used to be
a whole different thing.

921
01:19:19.519 --> 01:19:21.761
Strangers rested there.

922
01:19:21.854 --> 01:19:25.804
People leavin' messages.
Folks comin' and goin' all the time.

923
01:19:25.942 --> 01:19:29.642
It was a happy house when I first got
there with Denver strapped to my chest...

924
01:19:30.268 --> 01:19:32.104
waitin' on her daddy to come.

925
01:19:32.198 --> 01:19:34.107
Daddy.

926
01:19:34.200 --> 01:19:37.450
Halle bought Baby Suggs' freedom...

927
01:19:37.536 --> 01:19:40.323
but slavery done already
busted her legs...

928
01:19:40.943 --> 01:19:44.114
and busted her back.
hands. everything.

929
01:19:44.209 --> 01:19:47.245
When she come here. she ain't had
nothin' left to make no livin' with...

930
01:19:47.992 --> 01:19:50.249
besides her heart.

931
01:19:55.341 --> 01:19:58.259
Baby Suggs used to preach
right here.

932
01:20:00.183 --> 01:20:03.184
Let the children come.

933
01:20:03.311 --> 01:20:05.683
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Footsteps ]

934
01:20:07.815 --> 01:20:11.729
Let your mothers hear you laugh.

935
01:20:11.861 --> 01:20:14.268
[ Children Laughing ]

936
01:20:27.042 --> 01:20:29.912
Let the grown men come.

937
01:20:38.053 --> 01:20:42.133
Let your wives
and your children...

938
01:20:42.265 --> 01:20:44.637
see you dance.

939
01:20:47.770 --> 01:20:50.142
[ Crowd Cheering. Chattering ]

940
01:21:16.131 --> 01:21:20.508
Women! Women!

941
01:21:20.734 --> 01:21:24.435
I want you to weep!

942
01:21:24.472 --> 01:21:26.346
Just weep...

943
01:21:29.477 --> 01:21:31.386
for the living...

944
01:21:33.393 --> 01:21:35.303
for the dead.

945
01:21:37.234 --> 01:21:39.904
Weep.

946
01:22:06.096 --> 01:22:10.473
Grandma Baby used to say your daddy
was too good for this world.

947
01:22:10.600 --> 01:22:12.474
Remember?

948
01:22:13.603 --> 01:22:15.809
He was a good man.

949
01:22:15.938 --> 01:22:17.931
It scared her.

950
01:22:18.024 --> 01:22:22.816
She used to always fret and worry
he wasn't gonna make it through nothin'.

951
01:22:22.945 --> 01:22:25.317
He made it through a lot.

952
01:22:26.448 --> 01:22:29.319
Maybe Grandma Baby was right.

953
01:22:34.373 --> 01:22:36.282
Denver...

954
01:22:37.626 --> 01:22:40.995
your daddy ain't gonna
never show up here.

955
01:22:42.464 --> 01:22:45.334
- You understand?
- But--

956
01:22:48.053 --> 01:22:50.757
The day ain't gonna
never come...

957
01:22:50.889 --> 01:22:54.969
when Halle knocks on that door.

958
01:22:55.059 --> 01:22:56.968
Never.

959
01:23:09.657 --> 01:23:11.530
There--

960
01:23:20.798 --> 01:23:22.707
Mama!

961
01:23:39.435 --> 01:23:41.558
Paul!

962
01:23:41.687 --> 01:23:44.605
Paul D! Paul D!

963
01:23:44.732 --> 01:23:46.890
You here?

964
01:23:47.026 --> 01:23:51.403
[ Laughing ]
Where else would I be on a Sunday off?

965
01:23:51.530 --> 01:23:53.404
[ Water Splashing ]

966
01:24:01.623 --> 01:24:04.790
[ Panting ] You're here.

967
01:24:06.044 --> 01:24:07.918
Uh-huh.

968
01:24:09.214 --> 01:24:11.586
Why don't you come on in here?
[ Laughing ]

969
01:24:15.240 --> 01:24:17.128
Girls right behind me.

970
01:24:17.153 --> 01:24:19.027
I don't hear nobody.

971
01:24:20.933 --> 01:24:23.424
- I gotta cook.
- Me too.

972
01:24:32.903 --> 01:24:34.777
Yeah. yeah.

973
01:24:43.187 --> 01:24:45.457
I thought I'd make
some snap beans.

974
01:24:56.384 --> 01:24:58.957
- Fry up a little corn.
- Yeah.

975
01:25:03.849 --> 01:25:05.804
Paul D. stop it. Stop it.

976
01:25:05.893 --> 01:25:09.807
- [ Paul D Whispering ]
- Denver?

977
01:25:09.897 --> 01:25:13.646
- Beloved? That you?
- [ Paul D ] Shh. shh.

978
01:25:13.776 --> 01:25:17.109
- [ Sethe Slapping Paul D ]
- Paul D!

979
01:25:17.196 --> 01:25:19.319
[ Paul D Chuckling ]
Come on.

980
01:25:19.448 --> 01:25:21.322
[ Sethe Giggling ]

981
01:25:23.744 --> 01:25:26.698
[ Whimpering ]

982
01:25:30.667 --> 01:25:32.541
[ Crying ]

983
01:25:43.304 --> 01:25:45.096
[ Crying Continues ]

984
01:27:07.468 --> 01:27:09.342
[ Calling ]

985
01:27:25.069 --> 01:27:27.441
[ Beloved Wheezing ]

986
01:27:27.571 --> 01:27:30.774
That was real fine. Sethe.
Thank you.

987
01:27:30.908 --> 01:27:33.030
- Sure you got enough?
- Yes. ma'am.

988
01:27:33.160 --> 01:27:35.781
Bone-tired and river-whipped.

989
01:27:35.871 --> 01:27:37.780
[ Dishes Clattering ]

990
01:27:41.084 --> 01:27:42.958
[ Sethe Chattering ]

991
01:28:21.248 --> 01:28:23.655
- Paul D.
- [ Groaning ]

992
01:28:27.379 --> 01:28:30.498
Don't tell me I slept
in this chair the whole night.

993
01:28:30.590 --> 01:28:33.081
I'm not gonna say a thing.

994
01:28:33.217 --> 01:28:35.451
- Why you didn't rouse me?
- I did.

995
01:28:35.476 --> 01:28:37.530
I tried callin' you
two or three times.

996
01:28:37.555 --> 01:28:40.342
- I thought maybe you went out somewhere.
- Sorry. honey.

997
01:28:40.474 --> 01:28:44.139
- I'll make us some breakfast.
- You know somethin'?

998
01:28:44.356 --> 01:28:46.636
Breakfast can wait.
[ Chuckling ]

999
01:28:49.400 --> 01:28:53.896
- Paul! Paul D! Paul D!
- [ Paul D Snoring ]

1000
01:28:54.029 --> 01:28:57.149
What you doin'
in Baby Suggs' bed?

1001
01:28:57.241 --> 01:28:59.150
I don't know.

1002
01:29:00.661 --> 01:29:03.602
Like I'm havin' house fits.

1003
01:29:04.748 --> 01:29:07.859
It got me to move from bed...

1004
01:29:08.110 --> 01:29:09.767
to chair to bed.

1005
01:29:11.087 --> 01:29:12.996
Slept good though.

1006
01:29:14.507 --> 01:29:17.294
No. Come on now.
You gonna be late for work.

1007
01:29:18.300 --> 01:29:21.056
Come on. come on.
I got to get to work. So do you.

1008
01:29:23.391 --> 01:29:25.264
Come on.

1009
01:29:25.393 --> 01:29:28.062
Yeah. right.

1010
01:29:28.187 --> 01:29:30.892
- Come on. Beloved.
- Yeah.

1011
01:29:31.023 --> 01:29:32.897
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

1012
01:29:52.168 --> 01:29:55.443
[ Beloved ] Why don't the chickens
have no teeth?

1013
01:29:55.468 --> 01:29:58.126
[ Sethe Laughing ]

1014
01:29:58.258 --> 01:30:01.128
- [ Beloved Mumbling ]
- [ Sethe ] Whoo!

1015
01:30:01.260 --> 01:30:04.878
- Chicken has no teeth.
- [ Sethe Laughing ]

1016
01:30:05.345 --> 01:30:08.963
Mama's cookin' chicken!

1017
01:30:28.787 --> 01:30:31.657
[ Paul D Moaning ]

1018
01:30:39.547 --> 01:30:43.592
Oh. God. [ Gasps ]

1019
01:30:45.979 --> 01:30:47.888
Head hurts.

1020
01:31:44.570 --> 01:31:46.942
What you want in here?

1021
01:31:54.108 --> 01:31:58.945
I want you touch me...

1022
01:31:59.190 --> 01:32:02.310
on the inside part...

1023
01:32:02.335 --> 01:32:04.908
and call my name.

1024
01:32:05.046 --> 01:32:10.586
Good people take you in.
treat you good...

1025
01:32:10.718 --> 01:32:13.719
you oughta try to be good back.

1026
01:32:13.804 --> 01:32:16.046
You don't--

1027
01:32:16.182 --> 01:32:18.470
Sethe loves you...

1028
01:32:18.601 --> 01:32:20.759
as much as her own daughter.
you know that.

1029
01:32:20.895 --> 01:32:23.730
She don't love me
like I love her.

1030
01:32:23.814 --> 01:32:26.768
I don't love nobody but her.

1031
01:32:27.113 --> 01:32:29.320
Then what you come in here for?

1032
01:32:33.323 --> 01:32:38.287
I want you to touch me
on the inside part.

1033
01:32:38.312 --> 01:32:41.598
Go back in that house
and get in that bed.

1034
01:32:47.503 --> 01:32:52.249
You has to touch me
on the inside part.

1035
01:32:52.589 --> 01:32:55.508
You has to call me my name.

1036
01:32:55.962 --> 01:32:57.510
No!

1037
01:32:57.638 --> 01:33:00.262
- No.
- I'll go if you call it.

1038
01:33:00.346 --> 01:33:04.178
- No. Beloved.
- Please. call it.

1039
01:33:05.813 --> 01:33:07.686
Beloved.

1040
01:33:07.815 --> 01:33:09.688
[ Groaning ]

1041
01:33:11.151 --> 01:33:13.060
Beloved.

1042
01:33:17.824 --> 01:33:19.698
Red heart.

1043
01:33:20.827 --> 01:33:23.614
Red heart.

1044
01:33:23.897 --> 01:33:26.457
Red heart.

1045
01:33:26.893 --> 01:33:28.866
Red heart.

1046
01:33:29.002 --> 01:33:32.038
Red heart. Red heart.

1047
01:33:36.617 --> 01:33:38.833
[ Paul D ] Red heart.

1048
01:33:38.970 --> 01:33:41.840
Red heart. Red heart!

1049
01:33:42.284 --> 01:33:43.846
Red heart!

1050
01:33:43.940 --> 01:33:47.025
Red heart. Red heart.

1051
01:33:48.187 --> 01:33:50.891
[ Paul D Crying ]

1052
01:33:51.023 --> 01:33:52.897
[ Screaming ]

1053
01:33:57.612 --> 01:34:00.483
[ Crying Continues ]

1054
01:34:06.871 --> 01:34:09.658
Are there flowers in the dark?

1055
01:34:10.057 --> 01:34:11.931
There is.

1056
01:34:24.592 --> 01:34:30.346
- [ Steamship Whistling ]
- [ Man Yelling ]

1057
01:34:32.938 --> 01:34:34.847
[ Yelling Continues ]

1058
01:34:40.112 --> 01:34:43.029
[ Men Chattering ]

1059
01:34:43.173 --> 01:34:45.580
- Come on. Come on.
- Whoo-hoo!

1060
01:34:45.617 --> 01:34:49.615
[ Paul D Mumbling ]

1061
01:34:49.867 --> 01:34:53.031
Paul D! Wanna ride with us?

1062
01:34:53.124 --> 01:34:56.374
We got the wagon today.
Why don't we--

1063
01:35:15.854 --> 01:35:18.891
[ Whispering ]
If I could just tell her.

1064
01:35:39.294 --> 01:35:43.077
[ Paul D ] Now. Sethe. you ain't
gonna like what I'm about to say.

1065
01:35:44.841 --> 01:35:47.248
Somethin' is happening to me.

1066
01:35:47.343 --> 01:35:49.252
That girl do it.

1067
01:35:51.722 --> 01:35:56.763
Fixin' me. Yeah.
She fixed me. Sethe.

1068
01:35:56.852 --> 01:36:00.600
She fixed me.
and I can't break it.

1069
01:36:00.689 --> 01:36:03.097
She-She moved me
out of the house...

1070
01:36:03.179 --> 01:36:06.259
and then she-- she joined me.

1071
01:36:06.284 --> 01:36:08.157
No.

1072
01:36:10.157 --> 01:36:12.694
- Paul D?
- [ Dog Barking ]

1073
01:36:13.268 --> 01:36:14.700
Paul D?

1074
01:36:16.454 --> 01:36:18.761
Why. you make me feel
like a young girl...

1075
01:36:19.027 --> 01:36:22.751
comin' by to pick me up
after work.

1076
01:36:23.143 --> 01:36:26.002
Pupski.
There you go. Pupski.

1077
01:36:26.683 --> 01:36:31.421
Better watch out. I might start
lookin' forward to it.

1078
01:36:31.510 --> 01:36:33.550
You get off from work
early or what?

1079
01:36:35.306 --> 01:36:37.464
I took off early.

1080
01:36:37.558 --> 01:36:41.306
- [ Horse Whinnying ]
- Anything the matter?

1081
01:36:43.589 --> 01:36:45.017
In a way of speakin'.

1082
01:36:50.278 --> 01:36:54.406
Sethe. you ain't gonna like
what I'm about to say.

1083
01:36:56.743 --> 01:37:00.326
Well. say it. Paul D.
whether I like it or not.

1084
01:37:05.987 --> 01:37:07.496
I want you pregnant.

1085
01:37:17.915 --> 01:37:19.375
You want me pregnant?

1086
01:37:21.100 --> 01:37:24.350
Is that what
you come by here for?

1087
01:37:24.478 --> 01:37:27.763
Don't you think I'm a little too old
to start that all over again?

1088
01:37:27.898 --> 01:37:29.855
Th-Think about it.

1089
01:37:30.068 --> 01:37:31.978
[ Paul D Laughing ]

1090
01:37:39.200 --> 01:37:41.074
You crazy man.

1091
01:37:45.039 --> 01:37:46.913
Come on.

1092
01:37:47.041 --> 01:37:49.413
[ Laughing Continues ]

1093
01:38:00.763 --> 01:38:02.969
[ Sethe ]
What has got into you?

1094
01:38:03.098 --> 01:38:06.966
You need some babies
or somebody to play with.

1095
01:38:07.102 --> 01:38:11.230
I'm sure willin' to try.
I need a willin' partner though.

1096
01:38:11.255 --> 01:38:13.378
I'll say. I'll say.

1097
01:38:22.450 --> 01:38:24.324
Mercy.

1098
01:38:25.954 --> 01:38:28.575
Let's run. Let's run.

1099
01:38:28.665 --> 01:38:31.416
I've been on my feet all day.

1100
01:38:31.501 --> 01:38:33.992
Oh. where I been. Sethe?

1101
01:38:34.017 --> 01:38:37.351
Stop. Paul D.
My legs ain't made for this.

1102
01:38:37.590 --> 01:38:39.464
[ Laughing ]

1103
01:38:39.592 --> 01:38:42.842
♪ Hard work ain't easy ♪

1104
01:38:42.970 --> 01:38:47.015
♪ Dry bread ain't greasy ♪
[ Laughing ]

1105
01:38:47.252 --> 01:38:50.786
♪ Little rice. little bean ♪

1106
01:38:50.811 --> 01:38:52.768
Hey. Stamp! Stamp Paid!

1107
01:38:52.854 --> 01:38:54.977
I'm gonna take
this one home with me!

1108
01:38:55.113 --> 01:38:59.609
[ Yelling. Laughing ]

1109
01:39:00.106 --> 01:39:03.298
Hey. you like this work so much. maybe
you best get in the chute with the others.

1110
01:39:03.323 --> 01:39:05.446
You ain't got much more sense
than they do.

1111
01:39:05.471 --> 01:39:07.713
♪ No meat in between ♪♪

1112
01:39:08.419 --> 01:39:09.762
I ain't singin' about this!

1113
01:39:09.787 --> 01:39:13.141
If a man can make a plan.
the man can make the good times happen.

1114
01:39:13.166 --> 01:39:17.662
The man got plans?
You savin' up for a gold mine. boy?

1115
01:39:17.795 --> 01:39:21.246
Better than gold. Me and my woman's
plannin' on startin' a family.

1116
01:39:21.958 --> 01:39:24.735
Yeah. a new life. Born free!

1117
01:39:25.038 --> 01:39:27.465
Now. if that don't mean a good time.
I don't know what does.

1118
01:39:27.661 --> 01:39:30.282
Nothin' born free ever again.

1119
01:39:30.882 --> 01:39:32.679
What you talkin'?

1120
01:39:33.936 --> 01:39:36.509
I been bought and sold
five times.

1121
01:39:36.647 --> 01:39:40.062
The last time. to the Northpoint
Bank and Railway Company.

1122
01:39:40.471 --> 01:39:45.132
No more! I walk and I sleep
and I eat where I please.

1123
01:39:45.157 --> 01:39:47.146
I earn a free man's wage.

1124
01:39:47.282 --> 01:39:49.654
Nobody's gonna own us no more.

1125
01:39:49.784 --> 01:39:52.156
Nobody's gonna own
my children either.

1126
01:39:52.245 --> 01:39:54.818
No more! No more!

1127
01:39:54.956 --> 01:39:57.957
Children inherit
where they come from.

1128
01:39:58.042 --> 01:40:02.040
Just 'cause you can't see no chains
don't mean they not there.

1129
01:40:02.171 --> 01:40:06.632
And as long as the world is white.
that's where we stayin'.

1130
01:40:07.968 --> 01:40:10.175
Come on.
Let's go get somethin' to eat.

1131
01:40:10.200 --> 01:40:13.118
Come on. Come on.

1132
01:40:15.726 --> 01:40:18.051
[ Hogs Squealing ]

1133
01:40:20.858 --> 01:40:22.238
Mind if I join you?

1134
01:40:23.608 --> 01:40:26.645
Free country.
no matter what nobody say.

1135
01:40:34.946 --> 01:40:37.239
You don't know. do you. son?

1136
01:40:37.372 --> 01:40:39.779
Know what?

1137
01:40:41.083 --> 01:40:44.452
You one of Baby Suggs'
Sweet Home men. ain't ya?

1138
01:40:45.835 --> 01:40:46.911
Yes. sir.

1139
01:40:47.430 --> 01:40:51.258
Me. My brothers.
Her son. Halle.

1140
01:40:51.385 --> 01:40:53.923
- You knew Baby?
- Oh. yeah.

1141
01:40:54.013 --> 01:40:57.595
Baby Suggs Holy.
God rest her soul.

1142
01:40:57.724 --> 01:41:01.770
Yeah. Sethe told me
she died soft as cream.

1143
01:41:01.795 --> 01:41:04.765
Well. maybe on the outside.

1144
01:41:05.575 --> 01:41:07.471
Why is that?

1145
01:41:13.323 --> 01:41:15.730
[ Papers Shuffling ]

1146
01:41:22.999 --> 01:41:28.289
It was me who had brung Sethe across the
river when she run away from Sweet Home.

1147
01:41:31.132 --> 01:41:34.500
I was there the day it happened.

1148
01:41:39.848 --> 01:41:42.256
Who is it?

1149
01:41:42.351 --> 01:41:45.470
That there's a picture of Sethe.

1150
01:41:45.562 --> 01:41:47.471
Sethe?

1151
01:41:49.566 --> 01:41:52.483
[ Scoffs ]
That ain't her mouth.

1152
01:41:52.898 --> 01:41:55.861
I can see
why you may think it...

1153
01:41:56.193 --> 01:41:58.444
around the eyes.

1154
01:42:01.119 --> 01:42:04.819
B-But that there
ain't her mouth.

1155
01:42:07.458 --> 01:42:12.665
Besides. why would they put some
colored woman's picture in the paper?

1156
01:42:13.210 --> 01:42:15.714
You don't read. do you. son?

1157
01:42:21.930 --> 01:42:25.679
You want me to read to you?

1158
01:42:27.185 --> 01:42:29.557
[ Sweeping ]

1159
01:42:32.190 --> 01:42:34.562
[ Chattering. Distant ]

1160
01:43:05.889 --> 01:43:08.214
[ Horse Whinnying ]

1161
01:43:08.308 --> 01:43:12.602
Already fed the girls.
You eat?

1162
01:43:14.356 --> 01:43:17.060
Want something?

1163
01:43:42.091 --> 01:43:44.926
Best you come inside.

1164
01:44:04.447 --> 01:44:07.486
I don't have to tell you
about Sweet Home...

1165
01:44:07.615 --> 01:44:09.489
what it was.

1166
01:44:11.160 --> 01:44:16.285
Maybe you don't know what it was like
for me to get away from there.

1167
01:44:17.458 --> 01:44:20.909
I did it.
I got us all out.

1168
01:44:21.839 --> 01:44:25.464
Up until then. it was the only thing
I ever did on my own.

1169
01:44:25.549 --> 01:44:29.167
Me... usin' my own head.

1170
01:44:32.181 --> 01:44:35.098
But it was more than that.

1171
01:44:36.435 --> 01:44:39.270
I was-- I was big...

1172
01:44:40.024 --> 01:44:41.762
and wide. Paul.

1173
01:44:42.193 --> 01:44:47.531
So wide. when I stretched out my arms.
all my children could get in between.

1174
01:44:47.556 --> 01:44:51.312
Looked like I-- Looked like I loved 'em
more after we got here.

1175
01:44:51.413 --> 01:44:53.322
[ Chuckles ]

1176
01:44:53.409 --> 01:44:57.988
Maybe I just knew that long as we was
in Kentucky with Schoolteacher...

1177
01:44:58.584 --> 01:45:00.993
they really wasn't mine to love.

1178
01:45:01.125 --> 01:45:03.995
Look like when
I jumped off that wagon...

1179
01:45:04.086 --> 01:45:08.795
wasn't nobody in this world
I couldn't love if I want to.

1180
01:45:10.467 --> 01:45:12.923
Twenty-eight days.

1181
01:45:13.542 --> 01:45:17.051
Twenty-eight good days
of free life.

1182
01:45:18.183 --> 01:45:20.935
I'd wake up in the morning and...

1183
01:45:21.440 --> 01:45:25.141
decide for myself
what to do with the day.

1184
01:45:27.362 --> 01:45:29.859
Sometimes I-- I hear my boys--

1185
01:45:29.944 --> 01:45:33.894
hear 'em laughin' a laugh
I ain't never heard.

1186
01:45:33.919 --> 01:45:37.584
First I get scared. scared
somebody might hear 'em...

1187
01:45:38.207 --> 01:45:40.033
and get mad.

1188
01:45:40.501 --> 01:45:43.863
Then I remembered that if they laughed
that hard till it hurt...

1189
01:45:44.797 --> 01:45:47.415
that'd be the only hurt
they have all day.

1190
01:45:49.296 --> 01:45:52.048
And when the people
would gather--

1191
01:45:52.132 --> 01:45:55.715
they'd come from all around
to hear Baby Suggs Holy--

1192
01:45:55.803 --> 01:46:00.345
I seen and heard things
I ain't never seen before.

1193
01:46:03.226 --> 01:46:07.520
I seen what free Negroes
look like for the first time.

1194
01:46:09.316 --> 01:46:14.392
Here in this place.
we are flesh.

1195
01:46:15.202 --> 01:46:17.695
Flesh that weeps...

1196
01:46:17.782 --> 01:46:19.691
laughs...

1197
01:46:19.973 --> 01:46:22.619
dances barefoot in the grass.

1198
01:46:22.745 --> 01:46:25.699
[ Audience Murmuring Approval ]

1199
01:46:26.463 --> 01:46:29.324
Love your flesh.

1200
01:46:30.461 --> 01:46:32.916
Love it hard.

1201
01:46:33.047 --> 01:46:38.670
Yonder...
they do not love our flesh.

1202
01:46:38.802 --> 01:46:41.127
[ Man ] Amen.

1203
01:46:42.264 --> 01:46:47.091
[ Chuckling ]
Oh. my people...

1204
01:46:48.770 --> 01:46:52.554
they do not love your hands.

1205
01:46:54.484 --> 01:47:00.024
Those... they only use...

1206
01:47:00.156 --> 01:47:03.525
tie... bind...

1207
01:47:03.659 --> 01:47:05.985
chop off...

1208
01:47:06.120 --> 01:47:08.872
and leave empty.

1209
01:47:11.542 --> 01:47:14.626
Love your hands.

1210
01:47:18.090 --> 01:47:20.795
Raise them up...

1211
01:47:20.884 --> 01:47:23.802
and kiss them.

1212
01:47:24.930 --> 01:47:26.804
[ Kissing ]

1213
01:47:26.932 --> 01:47:29.470
[ Guffawing ]

1214
01:47:29.559 --> 01:47:32.975
[ All Laughing. Clapping ]

1215
01:47:34.272 --> 01:47:38.815
Twenty-eight days of... freedom.

1216
01:47:40.820 --> 01:47:43.821
On the 29th day. it was over.

1217
01:47:51.956 --> 01:47:54.328
[ Chopping ]

1218
01:47:55.543 --> 01:47:57.998
[ Whispering ] Outside.

1219
01:48:02.767 --> 01:48:04.760
[ Baby Crying ]

1220
01:48:04.785 --> 01:48:06.825
[ Chopping Continues ]

1221
01:48:13.560 --> 01:48:16.893
- ♪♪ [ Humming ]
- [ Crying Continues ]

1222
01:48:35.384 --> 01:48:39.658
[ Sethe Narrating ]
There's a look that white folks get.

1223
01:48:39.752 --> 01:48:44.045
Righteous look that's like
a flag goin' up a pole.

1224
01:48:46.895 --> 01:48:49.296
A righteousness that...

1225
01:48:49.428 --> 01:48:52.631
comes along with the whip
and the fist...

1226
01:48:52.764 --> 01:48:56.215
the burnin'. the lie.

1227
01:48:56.723 --> 01:48:59.554
Long before it happens
in the open.

1228
01:49:00.409 --> 01:49:02.854
No. no!

1229
01:49:02.941 --> 01:49:07.021
- Howard. Buglar. get in the shed!
- [ Crying ]

1230
01:49:07.111 --> 01:49:10.895
Get in the shed! Run!

1231
01:49:10.920 --> 01:49:12.959
[ Crying Continues ]

1232
01:49:14.535 --> 01:49:17.108
[ Screaming ] No!

1233
01:49:17.246 --> 01:49:20.413
Get in the shed! No!

1234
01:49:22.251 --> 01:49:27.589
[ Sethe. Distant ]
No! No! No! No!

1235
01:49:27.714 --> 01:49:30.751
[ Sethe Continues Screaming ]

1236
01:49:33.178 --> 01:49:35.301
[ Whinnying ]

1237
01:49:36.932 --> 01:49:42.222
[ Screaming Hysterically ]
No. no. no!

1238
01:49:42.312 --> 01:49:46.475
- [ Sethe ] No. no. no!
- [ Boy ] Mama!

1239
01:49:46.608 --> 01:49:49.443
[ Boys Screaming ]

1240
01:49:49.527 --> 01:49:52.065
[ Boy Screaming. Crying ]
Mama!

1241
01:49:52.155 --> 01:49:56.318
[ Screaming. Crying Continue ]

1242
01:50:01.372 --> 01:50:03.411
[ Baby Crying ]

1243
01:50:03.499 --> 01:50:06.143
- [ Grunting ]
- Sethe! Sethe! No!

1244
01:50:06.168 --> 01:50:09.646
- Sethe!
- [ Screaming ]

1245
01:50:09.671 --> 01:50:11.913
[ Sethe Panting ]

1246
01:50:12.007 --> 01:50:14.676
[ Coughing. Crying ]

1247
01:50:14.801 --> 01:50:17.008
God Almighty.

1248
01:50:17.137 --> 01:50:19.758
[ Denver Crying ]

1249
01:50:26.668 --> 01:50:29.183
What'd you go and do that for?

1250
01:50:30.082 --> 01:50:32.352
What'd you go and do that for?

1251
01:50:32.485 --> 01:50:35.320
[ Breathing Heavily ]

1252
01:50:39.216 --> 01:50:40.986
What'd you go and do that for?

1253
01:50:47.099 --> 01:50:49.666
[ Denver Continues Crying ]

1254
01:50:56.675 --> 01:50:58.549
[ Gasping ]

1255
01:50:58.677 --> 01:51:03.339
Y'all better go on.
Nothin' here to claim. I guess.

1256
01:51:04.199 --> 01:51:07.056
- Look like your business is over.
- [ Throwing Hat ]

1257
01:51:08.269 --> 01:51:10.345
Mine's started.

1258
01:51:11.439 --> 01:51:13.348
[ Spits ]

1259
01:51:14.501 --> 01:51:15.835
Animal.

1260
01:51:15.860 --> 01:51:18.565
[ Crying Continues ]

1261
01:51:27.580 --> 01:51:29.489
[ Baby Suggs Gasping ]

1262
01:51:29.582 --> 01:51:32.535
Oh. [ Continues Gasping ]

1263
01:51:32.626 --> 01:51:34.535
Oh.

1264
01:51:37.078 --> 01:51:38.493
Oh.

1265
01:51:38.518 --> 01:51:41.585
I'm going out of here.
I'll send for a wagon.

1266
01:51:43.125 --> 01:51:46.260
Howard. Howard! [ Wheezing ]

1267
01:51:46.315 --> 01:51:49.518
- Wake up. Buglar. Baby!
- [ Buglar Wheezing ]

1268
01:51:49.905 --> 01:51:52.217
Come on. sweetheart.
Wake up! Wake up!

1269
01:51:52.353 --> 01:51:54.560
- [ Moaning ]
- Oh!

1270
01:51:55.179 --> 01:51:56.895
I beg your pardon.

1271
01:51:57.025 --> 01:52:01.402
Sethe. you take my armload
and give me your'n.

1272
01:52:01.529 --> 01:52:06.238
- [ Boys Coughing ]
- [ Crying ]

1273
01:52:06.367 --> 01:52:11.705
[ Baby Suggs ]
I beg your pardon. I beg your pardon.

1274
01:52:12.177 --> 01:52:14.790
I beg your pardon.

1275
01:52:16.919 --> 01:52:19.706
Your love is too thick. Sethe.

1276
01:52:21.256 --> 01:52:24.590
Love is or it isn't. Paul D.

1277
01:52:24.676 --> 01:52:27.547
Thin love ain't no love at all.

1278
01:52:28.158 --> 01:52:30.093
I stopped him.

1279
01:52:30.953 --> 01:52:33.597
I put my babies
where'd they be safe.

1280
01:52:33.727 --> 01:52:37.060
Didn't work. though. did it?

1281
01:52:37.334 --> 01:52:40.396
Your boys are gone.
you don't know where.

1282
01:52:40.483 --> 01:52:46.023
One girl's dead. The other
can't get further than the yard.

1283
01:52:47.602 --> 01:52:49.891
How did it work?

1284
01:52:50.868 --> 01:52:53.359
They ain't at Sweet Home.

1285
01:52:54.017 --> 01:52:56.247
Schoolteacher ain't got 'em.

1286
01:52:56.332 --> 01:53:01.077
- Maybe there's worse.
- It ain't my job to know what's worse. Paul D.

1287
01:53:01.655 --> 01:53:06.512
It's my job to know what is and to keep my
children away from it. 'cause I'd rather know...

1288
01:53:06.537 --> 01:53:10.090
they at peace in heaven than live in
a hell here on Earth. so help me. Jesus.

1289
01:53:10.178 --> 01:53:13.629
- What you did was wrong. Sethe.
- I should've gone back there?

1290
01:53:14.162 --> 01:53:17.139
Took my babies
back to Sweet Home?

1291
01:53:17.227 --> 01:53:19.515
There could've been a way.
Some other way.

1292
01:53:19.646 --> 01:53:21.603
What way. Paul D?

1293
01:53:21.689 --> 01:53:25.307
You got two feet.
Sethe. not four.

1294
01:53:34.118 --> 01:53:36.823
You can set aside supper for me.

1295
01:53:41.709 --> 01:53:45.160
I might be late gettin' back.

1296
01:53:48.674 --> 01:53:52.339
After all
I just told you. Paul D...

1297
01:53:55.037 --> 01:53:58.380
and after you tellin' me
how many feet I got...

1298
01:53:59.291 --> 01:54:03.012
you think sayin' goodbye
is gonna break me into pieces?

1299
01:54:09.944 --> 01:54:12.517
You're a sweet man.

1300
01:54:24.483 --> 01:54:26.375
[ Door Shutting ]

1301
01:54:26.460 --> 01:54:29.129
So long. Paul D.

1302
01:54:46.355 --> 01:54:48.680
We could roast some taters.

1303
01:54:49.190 --> 01:54:52.855
Too late. Tomorrow.

1304
01:55:10.002 --> 01:55:13.287
♪♪ [ Humming Lullaby ]

1305
01:55:17.801 --> 01:55:20.208
♪♪ [ Continues ]

1306
01:55:32.857 --> 01:55:34.896
♪♪ [ Stops ]

1307
01:55:35.985 --> 01:55:38.939
I made that song up.

1308
01:55:39.426 --> 01:55:42.890
I made it up and sang it
to my children.

1309
01:55:42.992 --> 01:55:45.946
Nobody knows that song but...

1310
01:55:47.204 --> 01:55:49.612
me and my children.

1311
01:55:51.125 --> 01:55:53.698
I know.

1312
01:55:53.835 --> 01:55:56.789
♪♪ [ Resumes Humming ]

1313
01:56:17.275 --> 01:56:20.857
[ Muffled Humming. Wheezing ]

1314
01:56:51.182 --> 01:56:53.056
[ Gasping ]

1315
01:57:01.206 --> 01:57:04.041
You came back to me.

1316
01:57:06.989 --> 01:57:09.361
[ Softly ] Yeah.

1317
01:57:49.613 --> 01:57:54.275
- [ Beloved Snoring. Wheezing ]
- Ohh.

1318
01:57:54.410 --> 01:57:57.446
- Back stiff?
- Mmm. Yeah.

1319
01:57:59.498 --> 01:58:03.198
- Sleeping on the floor's supposed to be good for you.
- Hurt like the devil.

1320
01:58:04.202 --> 01:58:05.998
Should I wake her?

1321
01:58:06.129 --> 01:58:08.667
No. Let her rest.

1322
01:58:09.513 --> 01:58:11.429
She likes to see you off
in the morning.

1323
01:58:11.454 --> 01:58:14.302
I'm gonna let her. but first
get me that ham out of there.

1324
01:58:15.130 --> 01:58:19.091
I'm gonna make us a nice.
big breakfast against the cold outside.

1325
01:58:19.225 --> 01:58:22.819
- Won't you be late for work?
- First time I'll be late in 16 years.

1326
01:58:23.077 --> 01:58:24.664
It don't matter.

1327
01:58:24.689 --> 01:58:28.437
Whatever goes on out there goes on
with or without me showin' up on time.

1328
01:58:28.526 --> 01:58:30.767
The world is right here
in this room.

1329
01:58:30.903 --> 01:58:35.612
- Right here is all that is and all there needs to be.
- [ Stirring ]

1330
01:58:35.741 --> 01:58:41.032
- She ain't even mad at me. Not a bit.
- [ Continues Wheezing ]

1331
01:58:41.163 --> 01:58:43.286
[ Groaning ]

1332
01:58:52.090 --> 01:58:54.462
[ Girls Chattering. Distant ]

1333
01:58:57.720 --> 01:58:59.630
[ Chuckling ]

1334
01:59:01.349 --> 01:59:03.674
Whoo.

1335
01:59:19.611 --> 01:59:22.032
- [ Boy #1 ] Mama!
- [ Boy #2 ] Mama!

1336
01:59:24.935 --> 01:59:27.204
- Mama!
- Mama!

1337
01:59:27.332 --> 01:59:30.701
[ Footsteps Crunching In Snow ]

1338
01:59:32.420 --> 01:59:34.911
- Mama!
- Mama!

1339
01:59:46.267 --> 01:59:48.260
[ Chattering ]

1340
01:59:54.859 --> 01:59:57.432
[ Man ] Put it back in there.
Put it back.

1341
01:59:57.570 --> 02:00:00.480
[ Speaking German ]
That's it. You're late. You're fired.

1342
02:00:00.505 --> 02:00:02.774
That's all.
I-I-I've had it.

1343
02:00:02.799 --> 02:00:05.629
You make potato salad
always too sweet.

1344
02:00:05.654 --> 02:00:08.145
And you didn't make
the pies today.

1345
02:00:08.539 --> 02:00:12.157
You take home too much food. Where
are you going? Where are you going?

1346
02:01:02.757 --> 02:01:06.707
- My goodness. Is that--
- Yes. it is.

1347
02:01:11.933 --> 02:01:15.349
- Did you see that?
- What? That's a disgrace.

1348
02:01:18.522 --> 02:01:20.930
[ Chattering ]

1349
02:01:24.820 --> 02:01:26.943
Sethe.

1350
02:01:27.525 --> 02:01:31.357
[ Woman ]
Don't look now. but there is Sethe.

1351
02:01:41.086 --> 02:01:43.327
- Mm.
- Is she the one?

1352
02:02:00.730 --> 02:02:03.647
Will that be all. ma'am?

1353
02:02:03.733 --> 02:02:06.306
[ All Screaming ]

1354
02:02:06.443 --> 02:02:08.317
- [ Women ] ♪ To get my grip ♪
- [ Screaming ]

1355
02:02:08.437 --> 02:02:12.649
♪ I came back home just a-pullin'
the skiff. just a-pullin' the skiff ♪

1356
02:02:12.872 --> 02:02:15.610
♪ Went upstairs to make my bed ♪

1357
02:02:15.702 --> 02:02:18.739
♪ I made a mistake
and bumped my head ♪

1358
02:02:18.872 --> 02:02:21.908
♪ Just a-pullin' the skiff
Just a-pullin' the skiff ♪

1359
02:02:22.042 --> 02:02:25.327
[ Together ]
♪ I came downstairs to milk that cow ♪

1360
02:02:25.551 --> 02:02:28.666
♪ I made a mistake
and I milked that sow ♪

1361
02:02:28.691 --> 02:02:32.299
♪ Just a-pullin' the skiff
Just a-pullin' the skiff ♪

1362
02:02:32.336 --> 02:02:32.954
[ Screeching. Laughing ]

1363
02:02:32.979 --> 02:02:35.113
♪ Tomorrow. tomorrow
tomorrow never comes ♪

1364
02:02:35.138 --> 02:02:38.507
♪ Tomorrow. tomorrow
tomorrow never comes ♪

1365
02:02:38.599 --> 02:02:41.766
- [ Denver ] The best part.
- ♪♪ [ All Grunting In Tune ]

1366
02:02:41.894 --> 02:02:45.345
- ♪♪ [ Grunting Continues ]
- [ Beloved Babbling ]

1367
02:02:45.690 --> 02:02:49.238
- Look at my pretty baby. She's my best thing.
- Denver.

1368
02:02:49.263 --> 02:02:51.861
[ Beloved ]
♪ Tomorrow never come ♪

1369
02:02:51.946 --> 02:02:55.867
- Thank you. Mama.
- ♪ Tomorrow. tomorrow
tomorrow in the barn ♪♪

1370
02:02:55.892 --> 02:02:59.073
- [ Laughing ]
- ♪♪ [ Grunting ]

1371
02:03:09.170 --> 02:03:12.041
[ Beloved Babbling ]

1372
02:03:26.908 --> 02:03:28.436
This one?

1373
02:03:29.675 --> 02:03:32.455
- Would you wrap it. please?
- What's she doing?

1374
02:03:46.331 --> 02:03:48.573
[ Sethe Panting ]

1375
02:03:48.667 --> 02:03:51.371
The first day we got here
to Bluestone Road...

1376
02:03:51.461 --> 02:03:54.130
you dribbled clear spit
on my face.

1377
02:03:54.547 --> 02:03:59.131
Just like when you come back and drink
that water. it run down your chin.

1378
02:03:59.260 --> 02:04:01.668
I'd have recognized you
right off...

1379
02:04:01.804 --> 02:04:04.426
- [ Beloved Grunting ]
- but Paul D. he distract me.

1380
02:04:04.846 --> 02:04:06.596
Then later on...

1381
02:04:06.684 --> 02:04:11.262
when you asked me about them earrings
I used to dangle for you to play with...

1382
02:04:11.986 --> 02:04:14.309
- [ Babbling ]
- I'd have known that was you...

1383
02:04:14.441 --> 02:04:16.315
except for Paul D.

1384
02:04:18.320 --> 02:04:21.072
Looked to me like he wanted you out
from the beginning.

1385
02:04:21.156 --> 02:04:24.607
But I wouldn't let him.
What you think?

1386
02:04:24.701 --> 02:04:26.610
Hmm.

1387
02:04:27.359 --> 02:04:31.531
I mean. look how he run off first
he hear about you and me in the shed.

1388
02:04:32.959 --> 02:04:35.664
Too tough for him
to even listen to.

1389
02:04:36.796 --> 02:04:40.331
"My love too thick." he said.

1390
02:04:40.466 --> 02:04:43.171
What do he know about it?

1391
02:04:43.302 --> 02:04:45.628
[ Sethe ] ♪ High Johnny ♪

1392
02:04:45.909 --> 02:04:47.980
♪ Wide Johnny ♪

1393
02:04:48.182 --> 02:04:52.049
♪ Don't you leave my side ♪

1394
02:04:52.186 --> 02:04:55.306
♪ High Johnny ♪

1395
02:04:55.439 --> 02:04:58.191
♪ Wide Johnny ♪

1396
02:04:58.539 --> 02:05:03.821
♪ Sweet William. bend down low ♪

1397
02:05:06.617 --> 02:05:10.946
- ♪ Jack. we raise up high ♪
- [ Beloved Laughs ]

1398
02:05:11.671 --> 02:05:15.201
- ♪ Lambs wool ♪♪
- Why you hurt me?

1399
02:05:16.300 --> 02:05:19.201
Baby. you know.

1400
02:05:19.890 --> 02:05:22.215
Why you leave me?

1401
02:05:22.882 --> 02:05:25.551
Beloved. I wasn't never
gonna leave you.

1402
02:05:25.677 --> 02:05:27.550
Never.

1403
02:05:27.678 --> 02:05:31.237
But there wasn't no way I was gonna let
Schoolteacher come haul all of us off...

1404
02:05:31.324 --> 02:05:34.118
and measure your behind
'fore he tore it up.

1405
02:05:34.377 --> 02:05:37.726
- You leave me.
- No. baby. No.

1406
02:05:38.489 --> 02:05:42.766
See. my plan was to get us all over
to the other side where my own mammy is.

1407
02:05:42.901 --> 02:05:46.296
They stopped me from gettin' us
all there. but you had to be put...

1408
02:05:46.321 --> 02:05:49.108
where you'd be safe.
and I did that.

1409
02:05:49.866 --> 02:05:51.942
Now you come back...

1410
02:05:52.517 --> 02:05:55.250
and baby. I ain't gonna
never let you go.

1411
02:05:55.330 --> 02:05:56.953
I want a sweet.

1412
02:05:57.550 --> 02:05:59.620
Sweet?

1413
02:05:59.751 --> 02:06:02.206
[ Moaning. Grunting ] Sweet.

1414
02:06:02.295 --> 02:06:04.786
We don't have nothin' sweet
no more. baby.

1415
02:06:04.923 --> 02:06:08.291
Why you don't let me
eat the pie no more?

1416
02:06:08.426 --> 02:06:10.715
[ Plate Crashing ]

1417
02:06:10.845 --> 02:06:12.774
[ Moaning ]

1418
02:06:12.798 --> 02:06:14.993
Since Mama spent all the money.
we don't have no more.

1419
02:06:15.018 --> 02:06:18.716
[ Screaming ]
I want a sweet! I want a sweet!

1420
02:06:18.853 --> 02:06:22.612
- Sweet. sweet. sweet!
- Beloved? Beloved!

1421
02:06:22.637 --> 02:06:26.104
- [ Screaming Continues ]
- [ Sethe ] Beloved. baby?

1422
02:06:26.129 --> 02:06:28.370
Baby? Beloved!

1423
02:06:28.612 --> 02:06:32.312
[ Screaming. Crying ]

1424
02:06:36.016 --> 02:06:37.662
It's all right.

1425
02:06:40.123 --> 02:06:44.334
- [ Gasping ]
- I understand.

1426
02:06:44.461 --> 02:06:47.829
- [ Buzzing ]
- [ Whimpering ]

1427
02:07:04.730 --> 02:07:07.601
[ Buzzing Continues ]

1428
02:07:12.905 --> 02:07:15.146
[ Chirping ]

1429
02:07:21.997 --> 02:07:24.285
[ Moaning ]

1430
02:07:29.003 --> 02:07:31.292
[ Gagging ]

1431
02:07:35.603 --> 02:07:38.520
[ Screeching ]

1432
02:07:41.798 --> 02:07:43.921
[ Screeching Continues ]

1433
02:07:44.111 --> 02:07:45.985
Beloved?

1434
02:07:51.191 --> 02:07:54.109
[ Crying ]

1435
02:08:00.861 --> 02:08:02.770
[ Buzzing ]

1436
02:08:06.414 --> 02:08:08.241
[ Birds Chirping ]

1437
02:08:17.675 --> 02:08:19.833
[ Clucking ]

1438
02:08:53.877 --> 02:08:57.376
- [ Clanking ]
- [ Beloved Screaming ]

1439
02:09:07.640 --> 02:09:12.218
- [ Glass Breaking ]
- [ Beloved Screaming ]

1440
02:09:19.401 --> 02:09:21.275
Mama!

1441
02:09:24.799 --> 02:09:27.321
- [ Footsteps Above ]
- Mama!

1442
02:09:27.451 --> 02:09:29.906
- [ Metal Clanking ]
- [ Babbling ]

1443
02:09:29.995 --> 02:09:31.904
[ Groaning ]

1444
02:09:31.997 --> 02:09:34.404
[ Babbling Continues ]

1445
02:09:45.301 --> 02:09:47.210
Mama!

1446
02:09:48.596 --> 02:09:52.925
- [ Rattling ]
- [ Screaming. Babbling ]

1447
02:09:53.017 --> 02:09:54.926
Mama!

1448
02:09:59.081 --> 02:10:00.990
Mama!

1449
02:10:03.819 --> 02:10:06.191
[ Babbling Resumes ]

1450
02:10:17.082 --> 02:10:20.521
You best leave that quilt alone.

1451
02:10:21.439 --> 02:10:23.618
That's Grandma's quilt.

1452
02:10:27.165 --> 02:10:29.204
[ Gasping ]

1453
02:10:36.900 --> 02:10:41.484
[ Babbling ]
I want a sweet. Where is sweet?

1454
02:10:47.778 --> 02:10:50.150
[ Clattering. Distant ]

1455
02:10:58.038 --> 02:11:00.955
[ Chattering. Distant ]

1456
02:11:20.059 --> 02:11:24.934
[ Baby Suggs ] You mean I never
tell you about your daddy. Halle?

1457
02:11:25.064 --> 02:11:29.108
How he bought my freedom
with all that toil...

1458
02:11:29.234 --> 02:11:33.184
and never had a chance to see
the promised land for hisself?

1459
02:11:34.906 --> 02:11:39.153
Didn't I tell you
about the Bodwins...

1460
02:11:39.244 --> 02:11:41.913
who find me this here house...

1461
02:11:42.038 --> 02:11:44.873
and give me work in theirs?

1462
02:11:45.622 --> 02:11:50.165
How the Bodwins. they saved
your Mama's neck from the rope.

1463
02:11:51.255 --> 02:11:55.668
I never tell you all this?

1464
02:11:56.054 --> 02:11:59.583
Is that why you scared...

1465
02:11:59.608 --> 02:12:02.674
to go down them steps
and out yonder...

1466
02:12:02.766 --> 02:12:05.637
by yourself?

1467
02:12:06.710 --> 02:12:09.301
Is that why you didn't go back
to Miss Lady...

1468
02:12:09.714 --> 02:12:11.554
and finish learnin'
your letters?

1469
02:12:11.650 --> 02:12:15.730
You liked going there.
I remember.

1470
02:12:15.821 --> 02:12:21.111
Bein' with the other children.
All of a sudden you've stopped.

1471
02:12:24.370 --> 02:12:26.743
There was this boy...

1472
02:12:28.767 --> 02:12:31.375
and he said things about Mama.

1473
02:12:31.461 --> 02:12:34.748
- [ Gasping ]
- He said he could prove it.

1474
02:12:34.773 --> 02:12:38.248
[ Wheezing ]
My Jesus. my.

1475
02:12:40.177 --> 02:12:42.585
Come here. child.

1476
02:12:50.562 --> 02:12:53.397
We got to go sometime.

1477
02:12:53.482 --> 02:12:59.430
You got to go out yonder
by yourself sometime.

1478
02:13:00.822 --> 02:13:04.191
You got to go on
out of the yard.

1479
02:13:04.326 --> 02:13:06.781
Go on.

1480
02:14:28.990 --> 02:14:31.197
[ Hammering ]

1481
02:14:33.411 --> 02:14:35.783
[ Chattering ]

1482
02:14:42.712 --> 02:14:45.000
[ Man ] Come on. now.

1483
02:14:57.476 --> 02:14:59.599
[ Denver ]
I want to work. Miss Lady.

1484
02:15:01.049 --> 02:15:02.555
Work?

1485
02:15:03.846 --> 02:15:06.182
Start learnin'
your letters again?

1486
02:15:09.226 --> 02:15:11.234
I mean "work" work.

1487
02:15:13.283 --> 02:15:15.192
Well. Denver...

1488
02:15:17.443 --> 02:15:18.866
what can you do?

1489
02:15:24.210 --> 02:15:26.879
I can't do nothin'.

1490
02:15:26.963 --> 02:15:31.174
But I could learn it for you...
if you have a little extra.

1491
02:15:34.182 --> 02:15:35.426
Extra?

1492
02:15:38.839 --> 02:15:40.139
Food.

1493
02:15:45.355 --> 02:15:47.264
My mama...

1494
02:15:49.234 --> 02:15:52.235
she don't feel too good.

1495
02:15:53.405 --> 02:15:56.732
[ Sighs ] Oh. baby.

1496
02:16:11.505 --> 02:16:15.123
Eat. Bad Sethe.

1497
02:16:15.832 --> 02:16:18.337
Yes. Bad Sethe.

1498
02:16:24.351 --> 02:16:27.387
[ Beloved Babbling ]

1499
02:16:28.428 --> 02:16:30.938
[ Beloved ] Eat.

1500
02:16:31.150 --> 02:16:33.107
Eat.

1501
02:17:02.221 --> 02:17:04.094
[ Chirping ]

1502
02:17:08.053 --> 02:17:10.061
Ohh. honey.

1503
02:17:10.506 --> 02:17:12.379
What you got?

1504
02:17:28.871 --> 02:17:31.445
- [ Gasping ]
- Thank you. ma'am.

1505
02:17:31.582 --> 02:17:34.453
You're more than welcome.
my child.

1506
02:17:50.481 --> 02:17:52.390
Thank you.

1507
02:17:55.225 --> 02:17:57.765
[ Woman ]
No. no. That's not my bowl.

1508
02:17:57.899 --> 02:18:00.022
Sugar. mine got
a blue ring on it.

1509
02:18:00.110 --> 02:18:02.540
You wanna come in a spell?
Come on in.

1510
02:18:02.565 --> 02:18:05.277
I got some warm gingerbread.
You just go on in there.

1511
02:18:05.301 --> 02:18:06.487
Okay.

1512
02:18:13.539 --> 02:18:15.366
[ Rooster Crowing ]

1513
02:18:20.546 --> 02:18:22.918
[ Chattering ]

1514
02:18:45.153 --> 02:18:47.525
[ Dog Barking ]

1515
02:18:47.648 --> 02:18:52.696
Shh. Shh. Go on.
Move. Get off of me.

1516
02:18:52.727 --> 02:18:53.424
[ Barking Continues ]

1517
02:18:53.448 --> 02:18:56.532
You stink. and you messin'
up my dress. Stop it.

1518
02:18:56.664 --> 02:18:59.767
I'm tellin' you. get off of me.
Get off of me. now!

1519
02:18:59.861 --> 02:19:02.402
- [ Grunting ] Stop it.
- [ Growling ]

1520
02:19:02.834 --> 02:19:05.954
- How far you goin'. miss?
- I goin' to Cincinnati.

1521
02:19:11.596 --> 02:19:14.604
[ Driver ] That's as far as
we're goin'. miss. Get off.

1522
02:19:14.628 --> 02:19:15.931
Thank you.

1523
02:19:17.601 --> 02:19:20.934
- How's it goin'?
- Take care of yourself. all right?

1524
02:19:21.021 --> 02:19:25.019
Excuse me. I was lookin'
for the Bodwin's house.

1525
02:19:25.044 --> 02:19:28.979
You bugger off. you hear me?

1526
02:19:29.112 --> 02:19:31.817
[ Chattering ]

1527
02:19:45.343 --> 02:19:47.217
Yes?

1528
02:19:52.516 --> 02:19:54.349
What you want?

1529
02:19:56.221 --> 02:20:01.504
I wanted to see Mr and Mrs Bowman--
Mr and Mrs Bodwin.

1530
02:20:01.909 --> 02:20:03.510
Ms Bodwin.

1531
02:20:03.709 --> 02:20:07.759
They brother and sister. darlin'.
What you want with 'em?

1532
02:20:08.244 --> 02:20:13.319
I was lookin' for work. and I thought
that they might know about some.

1533
02:20:14.710 --> 02:20:17.195
Ohh...

1534
02:20:17.283 --> 02:20:20.658
you Baby Suggs' kid. ain't you?

1535
02:20:20.683 --> 02:20:25.038
- [ Chuckling ] Yes'm.
- I heard your mother took sick.

1536
02:20:25.959 --> 02:20:28.950
- Is that so?
- Yes'm.

1537
02:20:30.337 --> 02:20:34.287
Well. come on in.
You're lettin' in flies. Come on.

1538
02:20:36.969 --> 02:20:42.119
You know what? I been here since I'm
14. and I can remember like yesterday...

1539
02:20:42.144 --> 02:20:46.386
when Baby Suggs Holy came here
and sat right where you are.

1540
02:20:46.684 --> 02:20:51.270
White man. name of Garner. brought her.
He and Mr Bodwin was good friends.

1541
02:20:51.670 --> 02:20:55.166
That's how she got that house
you all live in. Other things too.

1542
02:20:55.190 --> 02:20:56.422
Yes'm.

1543
02:20:56.446 --> 02:21:01.024
I never went to those woodland services.
but she was always nice to me.

1544
02:21:01.117 --> 02:21:04.616
Always.
Never be another like her.

1545
02:21:05.437 --> 02:21:06.884
I miss her.

1546
02:21:07.039 --> 02:21:12.081
Bet you do. Everybody miss her.
That was a good woman.

1547
02:21:13.963 --> 02:21:15.920
Well...

1548
02:21:16.301 --> 02:21:21.251
I don't know whether the Bodwins think so or
not. but they sure could use some extra help.

1549
02:21:21.276 --> 02:21:23.814
- [ Both Chuckling ]
- You think?

1550
02:21:23.839 --> 02:21:27.133
Especially at night.
when it's no good for me to come.

1551
02:21:27.491 --> 02:21:31.395
It'll take some convincin'.
but maybe you could come after supper.

1552
02:21:31.817 --> 02:21:35.607
Take care of your mama
during the day. How's that?

1553
02:21:35.734 --> 02:21:38.853
- Fine.
- [ Chuckling ]

1554
02:21:38.987 --> 02:21:40.860
But what would I do at night?

1555
02:21:40.989 --> 02:21:45.050
- Just be here in case.
- In case what?

1556
02:21:45.075 --> 02:21:50.544
In case the house burned down or bad weather slopped
the roads up so bad I can't get here on time.

1557
02:21:50.639 --> 02:21:53.038
Or late guests needed
cleanin' up after.

1558
02:21:53.063 --> 02:21:54.951
Anything.

1559
02:21:55.044 --> 02:21:59.172
[ Snickering ] Don't ask me
what white folks need at night.

1560
02:22:01.513 --> 02:22:04.358
- They good white folk?
- Oh. yeah. They good.

1561
02:22:04.383 --> 02:22:08.341
Can't say they ain't good. I wouldn't trade
'em for another pair. I tell you that.

1562
02:22:09.021 --> 02:22:13.813
But you come back in a few days.
Give me a chance to lead up to it.

1563
02:22:13.937 --> 02:22:16.392
All right?

1564
02:22:20.110 --> 02:22:22.683
What is it. child?

1565
02:22:23.863 --> 02:22:27.197
What's the trouble with Sethe?

1566
02:22:29.327 --> 02:22:31.200
[ Whimpering ]

1567
02:22:31.412 --> 02:22:33.452
[ Chattering ]

1568
02:22:35.374 --> 02:22:38.311
Is it really the daughter. Janey?
The killed one?

1569
02:22:38.336 --> 02:22:40.535
That's what the girl say.

1570
02:22:40.671 --> 02:22:44.254
- How do you know it's her?
- It's sittin' there. Lucille.

1571
02:22:44.848 --> 02:22:47.217
It sleeps. eats and raises hell.

1572
02:22:47.242 --> 02:22:49.809
- I'll be. A baby.
- [ All Murmuring ]

1573
02:22:49.834 --> 02:22:54.135
Nah. It's grown. It's the age
it would've been had it lived.

1574
02:22:54.160 --> 02:22:54.708
Mercy.

1575
02:22:54.732 --> 02:22:57.602
What you talkin' about?
You talkin' about flesh?

1576
02:22:57.627 --> 02:23:01.701
I'm talkin' about flesh...
and it's whoopin' her...

1577
02:23:01.807 --> 02:23:03.916
- [ Women Gasping ]
- like she was batter.

1578
02:23:04.161 --> 02:23:09.156
- I guess she had it comin' a little.
- Nobody got that comin'.

1579
02:23:10.047 --> 02:23:14.595
But Ella. you just don't up
and kill your children.

1580
02:23:14.620 --> 02:23:19.108
No. and the children can't just up
and kill the mama.

1581
02:23:19.133 --> 02:23:22.364
Them that die bad
don't stay in the ground.

1582
02:23:22.389 --> 02:23:24.678
[ All Commenting ]

1583
02:23:28.884 --> 02:23:31.042
[ Sethe Muttering ]

1584
02:23:31.136 --> 02:23:33.425
[ Chopping ]

1585
02:23:35.932 --> 02:23:38.602
[ Beloved Snorting ]

1586
02:23:39.285 --> 02:23:41.348
[ Sethe ] Schoolteacher--

1587
02:23:42.044 --> 02:23:43.953
Mama?

1588
02:23:44.825 --> 02:23:47.602
Nobody ain't makin' nothin'.

1589
02:23:47.735 --> 02:23:50.689
- Nobody.
- Mama. I'm going out now.

1590
02:23:50.780 --> 02:23:53.105
[ Continues Muttering ]

1591
02:23:53.241 --> 02:23:55.696
[ Chopping Continues ]

1592
02:23:56.016 --> 02:23:59.450
I got a job workin' nights
over at the Bodwins.

1593
02:24:01.222 --> 02:24:03.963
Mr Bodwin's coming
to pick me up now.

1594
02:24:06.449 --> 02:24:09.787
Writin' my baby's
characteristics! [ Grunts ]

1595
02:24:10.288 --> 02:24:12.046
Lay that down.

1596
02:24:13.641 --> 02:24:15.218
We have money now.

1597
02:24:17.389 --> 02:24:20.259
[ Muttering Continues ]

1598
02:24:21.531 --> 02:24:23.358
Mama!

1599
02:24:29.609 --> 02:24:31.648
[ Muttering ]

1600
02:24:32.737 --> 02:24:35.192
[ Beloved Wheezing ]

1601
02:24:55.103 --> 02:24:56.406
Hey.

1602
02:25:06.875 --> 02:25:08.749
[ Snorting ]

1603
02:25:54.649 --> 02:25:56.523
[ Sniffling ]

1604
02:25:58.695 --> 02:26:01.565
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

1605
02:26:04.367 --> 02:26:07.237
[ Agitated Chattering ]

1606
02:26:14.918 --> 02:26:17.326
It's comin' out. It's over.

1607
02:26:17.421 --> 02:26:20.920
[ Chanting ]

1608
02:26:33.186 --> 02:26:35.807
[ Chanting Continues ]

1609
02:26:40.568 --> 02:26:44.103
- [ All Murmuring ]
- [ Woman ] Help us. help us.

1610
02:26:44.238 --> 02:26:46.112
Ohh!

1611
02:26:46.240 --> 02:26:48.731
Ohh. amen!

1612
02:26:48.868 --> 02:26:51.323
[ Chanting ]

1613
02:26:51.454 --> 02:26:54.371
[ Crying Out ]

1614
02:26:54.456 --> 02:26:58.731
- [ All Joining In ]
- Help us. Jesus!

1615
02:26:58.756 --> 02:27:02.161
[ Crying Intensifies ]

1616
02:27:02.297 --> 02:27:04.171
[ Screaming ]

1617
02:27:04.299 --> 02:27:07.662
Jesus. Jesus. Jesus.

1618
02:27:07.687 --> 02:27:09.974
- [ Woman ] ♪ I heard the voice ♪
- Yes.

1619
02:27:09.999 --> 02:27:13.596
- I heard the voice.
- ♪ I heard the voice ♪

1620
02:27:13.725 --> 02:27:18.351
- I heard the voice.
- ♪ I heard the voice ♪

1621
02:27:20.398 --> 02:27:24.016
♪ I heard the voice say ♪

1622
02:27:24.620 --> 02:27:28.903
♪ Come unto me and rest ♪

1623
02:27:28.990 --> 02:27:32.441
[ All. Growing Louder ]
♪ I ♪

1624
02:27:32.713 --> 02:27:35.780
- ♪ Heard ♪
- [ Woman ] ♪ The voice ♪

1625
02:27:35.913 --> 02:27:39.561
♪ The ♪

1626
02:27:39.586 --> 02:27:41.918
♪ Voice ♪

1627
02:27:42.539 --> 02:27:45.834
♪ Of ♪

1628
02:27:45.964 --> 02:27:51.718
- ♪ Jesus ♪
- [ Wheezing ]

1629
02:27:52.239 --> 02:27:55.178
♪ Say ♪

1630
02:27:55.742 --> 02:27:57.513
♪ Come ♪

1631
02:27:57.642 --> 02:28:04.851
♪ Un-to ♪

1632
02:28:04.876 --> 02:28:08.057
♪ Me ♪

1633
02:28:08.194 --> 02:28:11.064
♪ And ♪

1634
02:28:11.197 --> 02:28:14.648
♪ Rest ♪

1635
02:28:14.751 --> 02:28:18.153
- [ Woman ] ♪ Lay down. thou weary one ♪
- It's all right.

1636
02:28:18.287 --> 02:28:24.159
♪ Lay down thy head
upon my breast ♪

1637
02:28:24.784 --> 02:28:27.869
[ All ] ♪ Lay ♪

1638
02:28:28.005 --> 02:28:30.674
♪ Down ♪

1639
02:28:31.319 --> 02:28:34.084
♪ Thou ♪

1640
02:28:34.219 --> 02:28:40.672
♪ Weary ♪

1641
02:28:40.697 --> 02:28:43.809
♪ One ♪

1642
02:28:44.178 --> 02:28:46.973
- Mama?
- ♪ Lay ♪

1643
02:28:47.005 --> 02:28:49.208
- [ Snorting ]
- ♪ Down ♪

1644
02:28:49.233 --> 02:28:51.689
- ♪♪ [ Trails Off ]
- [ Murmuring ]

1645
02:28:51.714 --> 02:28:55.899
[ Gasping. Screaming ]

1646
02:28:56.032 --> 02:28:59.780
- [ Woman ] ♪ I came to Jesus ♪
- [ Grunting ]

1647
02:28:59.910 --> 02:29:03.753
- Oh. Lord. please.
- ♪ As I was ♪

1648
02:29:03.778 --> 02:29:07.612
♪ The weary one who said ♪

1649
02:29:07.637 --> 02:29:11.239
♪ I ♪

1650
02:29:11.264 --> 02:29:13.459
♪ Came ♪

1651
02:29:13.602 --> 02:29:16.652
♪ To ♪

1652
02:29:16.677 --> 02:29:23.265
♪ Je-sus ♪

1653
02:29:23.391 --> 02:29:26.345
♪ As ♪

1654
02:29:26.436 --> 02:29:30.101
♪ I ♪

1655
02:29:30.231 --> 02:29:32.271
♪ Was ♪

1656
02:29:33.568 --> 02:29:39.584
♪ He ♪

1657
02:29:39.609 --> 02:29:43.572
♪ Had ♪

1658
02:29:43.702 --> 02:29:50.059
♪ Hold and ♪

1659
02:29:50.084 --> 02:29:51.993
- ♪ Said ♪
- No.

1660
02:29:52.127 --> 02:29:54.167
- No. no. no. no.
- ♪ Tilt your eyes down low?

1661
02:29:54.192 --> 02:29:56.231
No. no. no. no.

1662
02:29:56.465 --> 02:29:58.829
[ Screeching ]

1663
02:29:58.854 --> 02:30:00.728
[ Crying ]

1664
02:30:01.335 --> 02:30:03.336
- Mama?
- ♪ I ♪♪

1665
02:30:04.162 --> 02:30:06.306
Mama?

1666
02:30:07.123 --> 02:30:09.599
- [ Continues Screaming ]
- Mama. that's Mr Bodwin!

1667
02:30:09.727 --> 02:30:12.812
- ♪♪ [ Singing Continues ]
- Mama!

1668
02:30:12.939 --> 02:30:15.512
Mama!

1669
02:30:17.151 --> 02:30:21.196
- Mama!
- No. no. no! No. no. no!

1670
02:30:21.221 --> 02:30:26.346
- No!
- Mama! Mama!

1671
02:30:26.577 --> 02:30:30.621
- [ All Yelling ]
- [ Sethe Whimpering ]

1672
02:30:36.086 --> 02:30:38.043
[ Screaming ]

1673
02:30:42.922 --> 02:30:45.329
[ Screaming Stops ]

1674
02:30:52.685 --> 02:30:55.057
[ Birds Chirping ]

1675
02:31:04.739 --> 02:31:06.648
[ Chirping Continues ]

1676
02:31:06.741 --> 02:31:09.658
♪♪ [ Girl Humming ]

1677
02:31:20.837 --> 02:31:23.209
♪♪ [ Humming Continues ]

1678
02:31:51.784 --> 02:31:54.191
[ Hammering ]

1679
02:31:54.286 --> 02:31:56.658
[ Chattering ]

1680
02:32:22.696 --> 02:32:25.614
Paul D? Is that you?

1681
02:32:31.433 --> 02:32:33.591
Good morning.

1682
02:32:34.854 --> 02:32:37.281
Well. it is now.

1683
02:32:39.705 --> 02:32:42.990
- How you gettin' along?
- Don't pay to complain.

1684
02:32:43.125 --> 02:32:46.674
- Yeah. Right. You on your way home?
- No.

1685
02:32:46.952 --> 02:32:49.527
I got an afternoon job
at the shirt factory.

1686
02:32:50.036 --> 02:32:52.667
I figure between that
and my night work at the Bodwins...

1687
02:32:52.801 --> 02:32:55.837
I might be able to put
somethin' aside for me and Mama.

1688
02:32:56.376 --> 02:32:58.211
They treatin' you right
over at the Bodwins?

1689
02:32:58.235 --> 02:32:59.867
Mm-hmm. More than all right.

1690
02:33:00.250 --> 02:33:02.596
Miss Bodwin. she teachin' me stuff.
Book stuff.

1691
02:33:02.727 --> 02:33:05.139
She say I might go
to Oberlin College.

1692
02:33:06.302 --> 02:33:08.229
That's fine. mighty fine.

1693
02:33:11.027 --> 02:33:12.936
Well.

1694
02:33:12.961 --> 02:33:16.320
[ Stammering ]
Your mother all right?

1695
02:33:21.328 --> 02:33:25.954
No. She's not a bit all right.

1696
02:33:26.489 --> 02:33:30.080
She hasn't gotten out of bed
since that day.

1697
02:33:32.537 --> 02:33:36.170
Think I should stop by?
Think she'd welcome it?

1698
02:33:38.428 --> 02:33:40.800
I don't know.

1699
02:33:44.006 --> 02:33:46.431
I think I lost my mama. Paul D.

1700
02:33:49.637 --> 02:33:52.142
Th-That girl.
You know. Beloved.

1701
02:33:53.818 --> 02:33:57.187
She-She gone like they say?

1702
02:33:57.768 --> 02:34:00.731
Haven't seen her since that day.

1703
02:34:01.441 --> 02:34:04.946
Mama say she gone.
She can feel it.

1704
02:34:05.695 --> 02:34:09.032
You think she sure enough
your sister?

1705
02:34:09.958 --> 02:34:11.867
At times.

1706
02:34:13.003 --> 02:34:15.245
At other times...

1707
02:34:17.924 --> 02:34:19.798
I think she was more.

1708
02:34:24.172 --> 02:34:27.304
But who would know that
better than you. Paul D?

1709
02:34:27.925 --> 02:34:30.304
You sure enough knew her.

1710
02:34:30.436 --> 02:34:34.137
- Well. if you want my opinion--
- I don't.

1711
02:34:34.273 --> 02:34:36.681
I have my own.

1712
02:34:36.817 --> 02:34:39.531
- ♪♪ [ Woman Vocalizing ]
- You grown.

1713
02:34:39.905 --> 02:34:41.444
Yes. sir.

1714
02:34:44.749 --> 02:34:48.118
Well. good luck with your job.

1715
02:34:48.245 --> 02:34:50.534
Thank you.

1716
02:34:50.664 --> 02:34:53.416
♪♪ [ Vocalizing Continues ]

1717
02:34:55.971 --> 02:34:57.745
Bye. now.

1718
02:34:57.838 --> 02:35:00.791
[ Man ] Watch your step.

1719
02:35:06.650 --> 02:35:08.635
Paul D?

1720
02:35:11.594 --> 02:35:13.057
You don't have to stay away.

1721
02:35:15.765 --> 02:35:18.250
But you watch how you talk
to my mama. you hear?

1722
02:35:19.143 --> 02:35:20.397
Don't worry.

1723
02:35:20.539 --> 02:35:22.911
[ Horse Whinnying ]

1724
02:35:23.028 --> 02:35:26.232
[ Man ] Hey. Miss Denver!
Wait up!

1725
02:35:26.365 --> 02:35:28.654
Hi.

1726
02:35:35.207 --> 02:35:37.116
Watch it. miss.

1727
02:35:45.633 --> 02:35:48.006
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

1728
02:35:49.471 --> 02:35:51.344
Ohh.

1729
02:35:56.894 --> 02:35:58.851
♪♪ [ Vocalizing Ends ]

1730
02:36:53.115 --> 02:36:55.985
[ Heavy Breathing ]

1731
02:37:04.630 --> 02:37:05.810
Sethe?

1732
02:37:16.304 --> 02:37:18.178
Paul D?

1733
02:37:30.484 --> 02:37:32.524
[ Sighs ]

1734
02:37:36.782 --> 02:37:39.154
[ Chuckling ]

1735
02:37:42.663 --> 02:37:44.572
You shaved.

1736
02:37:46.666 --> 02:37:50.082
Yeah. Look bad?

1737
02:37:52.046 --> 02:37:53.503
Lookin' good.

1738
02:37:54.178 --> 02:37:56.419
[ Guffawing ]

1739
02:37:56.816 --> 02:37:58.725
Devil's confusion.

1740
02:38:16.612 --> 02:38:21.108
- I seen Denver. She tell ya?
- [ Gasping ]

1741
02:38:22.660 --> 02:38:25.160
You gotta get up
from here. girl.

1742
02:38:28.999 --> 02:38:34.337
Look. Denver be here in the day.
I'll be here at night.

1743
02:38:34.797 --> 02:38:37.172
I'm gonna take care
of you. ya hear?

1744
02:38:37.257 --> 02:38:39.582
Startin' now.

1745
02:38:48.476 --> 02:38:52.010
What. baby? What?

1746
02:38:58.294 --> 02:39:00.635
[ Crying ] She leave me.

1747
02:39:03.427 --> 02:39:05.030
She gone again.

1748
02:39:05.159 --> 02:39:07.780
Oh. girl. Don't cry.

1749
02:39:09.634 --> 02:39:11.570
She leave me.

1750
02:39:12.326 --> 02:39:14.864
Sethe. Sethe.

1751
02:39:15.796 --> 02:39:17.869
[ Voice Breaking ] Paul...

1752
02:39:18.289 --> 02:39:21.663
she my best thing.

1753
02:39:24.302 --> 02:39:27.303
You your best thing. Sethe.

1754
02:39:30.892 --> 02:39:32.968
You are.

1755
02:39:37.148 --> 02:39:39.057
Me?

1756
02:39:42.010 --> 02:39:44.417
Me? [ Gasping ]

1757
02:39:52.120 --> 02:39:56.912
And the beat.
beat of your heart.

1758
02:39:57.000 --> 02:40:00.618
[ Audience Applauding.
Murmuring Approval ]

1759
02:40:00.754 --> 02:40:03.920
- ♪♪ [ Chorus Vocalizing ]
- Love it...

1760
02:40:04.048 --> 02:40:06.255
more than the lungs...

1761
02:40:06.384 --> 02:40:09.800
that need yet...

1762
02:40:09.929 --> 02:40:12.800
to breathe free air;

1763
02:40:14.100 --> 02:40:16.591
more than the womb...

1764
